title: mama j's mexican pie
directions: Put into pie dish in order listed.
Put in 400° oven until cheese melts.
Serve with Doritos.

title: apple crisp
directions: Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on package and cook in a 9 x 13-inch pan. While still hot, poke holes in cake.
Mix cream of coconut and Eagle Brand milk together and pour over cake.
Cool cake, then put Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle coconut over the Cool Whip.
Better if it sets a day or so before serving.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chicken and cheese enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In center of each tortilla, place 1/4 cup chicken (chopped), 2 tablespoons cheese and 2 tablespoons salsa. Roll up and arrange seam-side down in a casserole dish.
Top with remaining salsa and cheese.
Bake about 25 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: molasses oat muffins
directions: To toast oats, spread onto ungreased cake pan. Bake at 350° for 14 to 18 minutes; cool. In medium bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon. Stir in sugar and toasted oats. In small bowl, beat egg. Add milk and molasses to egg; beat well. Add to flour mixture. Add oil. Stir until dry ingredients are moistened. Fill muffin tins sprayed with cooking spray 2/3 full. Bake in preheated 400° oven 15 to 18 minutes.

title: cranberry pecan stuffing
directions: In a 4 quart saucepan, saute celery and onion in margarine until tender.
Add broth; heat to boiling.
Remove from heat; add stuffing, cranberries and pecans.
Mix well.
Use to stuff a 12 to 14 lb. turkey, or bake in a lightly greased baking dish at 400° until browned, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Start oven at 375° and grease shallow pan.
Put both kinds of bread in large bowl.
Pour 1 cup water over bread and let soak for several minutes.
Then mash fine with fork.
Combine meat, bread, parsley, chopped onion,
Parmesan cheese, egg, salt and pepper. Shape into loaf.
Bake 30 minutes.
Pour tomato sauce or soup on. Sprinkle oregano and bake 30 minutes more.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Mix flour, baking powder, sugar and milk.
Pour into baking dish.
Place fruit in the middle of the baking dish.
Do not stir.
Place in 375° preheated oven. Bake for 35 minutes, until golden brown.

title: louisiana hayride bean soup
directions: Note:
When I use picante and salty ham, I don't add any extra salt.

title: hershey refrigerator pie
directions: Blend cream cheese, chocolate syrup and Cool Whip thoroughly. Add pecans.
Spread into pie shell and top with remaining Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Refrigerate.
May be frozen for future use.

title: stir-fried pork and rice
directions: Use skillet to brown cut up chops in oil.
Let simmer, covered, until completely done.
Prepare Rice-A-Roni according to box directions.
Reduce the water suggested on the box for fluffier rice.
Combine rice with meat and mix well.
Add egg. Stir frequently.
Serve with cooked Chinese vegetables poured on top of rice/chop mixture.

title: cream cheese tarts
directions: Cream the cheese; add eggs and sugar.
Beat.
Add vanilla and beat well.

title: little wieners
directions: Put in crock-pot and heat.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Simmer mushrooms and grated lemon rind 10 minutes.
Cook noodles while mushrooms simmer.
Add heavy cream to mushrooms.
Stir and simmer 10 minutes.
Add noodles; toss and sprinkle in Parmesan cheese.
Toss again and serve.
Serves 6.

title: oriental salad
directions: Brown Ramen noodles (noodles only), save seasoning packets. Put sesame seeds in butter.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown beef in a 3-quart saucepan.
Drain off fat.
Add sauce and water.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients for filling (except lasagna noodles).
Pour about 1 cup of mixture on bottom of casserole dish.
Layer 3 pieces of noodles.
Cover with about 1 1/2 cups of sauce.
Spread 1/2 of cheese filling over sauce.
Repeat layers of lasagna, sauce and cheese filling.
Top with layer of lasagna and remaining sauce. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Remove foil and bake about 10 minutes longer.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt into a large mixing bowl.
Make a hole in the center and add oil, water, pumpkin, vanilla and eggs.
Beat until well mixed.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mr. mom's breakfast tortillas
directions: Heat tortillas in 350° oven, about 3 minutes if you like them soft, or 5 minutes if you like them crisper.
In the meantime, cook bacon until crisp.
Scramble and cook the eggs in a frying pan according to your taste.
Place one slice of bacon in each tortilla.
Spoon scrambled eggs over bacon.
Sprinkle with cheese and your favorite toppings.
Roll them up and enjoy!

title: speedway batter rolls
directions: Pour water into slightly warm mixing bowl.
Dissolve yeast; stir well.
Add milk, shortening, egg and dry ingredients.

title: rice pudding
directions: Place rice, milk and salt in a large pan; begin to cook over medium heat.
When milk is warm, add sugar and continue to cook slowly, stirring every 5 to 10 minutes.
Requires 1 to 1 1/2 hours of cooking.
Add raisins halfway through cooking.
When rice is thick, add ice cream and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Let cool in refrigerator.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: some of this and that dessert
directions: Spray a 9 x 14-inch pan with Pam.
Layer in following order: apple filling, crushed pineapple, brown sugar, cake mix, coconut and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cut into 24 small squares.
Can be eaten hot or cold.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chinese-style chicken dinner
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients in hot oil in a skillet over high heat for 5 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Remove from skillet. Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Saute chicken in drippings in skillet until tender.
Combine cornstarch, soy sauce and chicken broth, stirring until cornstarch dissolves.
Add to chicken and stir until mixture begins to bubble.
Cook 1 minute.
Stir constantly.
Return vegetables to skillet.
Stir until heated. Serve over rice.
Makes approximately 6 servings.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, cheese, onion and mayonnaise.
Place in casserole.
Crush crackers and sprinkle over vegetables.
Pour melted oleo over crackers.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain green beans and corn.
Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake for 1 hour.
Crush Ritz crackers; mix with melted butter.
Spread over casserole.
Bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; add sauce and simmer 10 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Mix cream cheese and sour cream.
Place noodles in greased baking dish.
Layer cream cheese mixture with meat sauce and Cheddar cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: marinated pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over pork chops.
Cover and refrigerate for about 8 hours.
Serves 6.

title: peanut patties
directions: Mix together all ingredients and cook for 1 hour over low heat. Add 1 teaspoon Parkay and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Add few drops red food coloring.
Beat until creamy and drop on cookie sheet lined with foil to form patties.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain liquid from beets into saucepan.
Blend in cornstarch and heat until thickened.
Add sugar, margarine and vinegar.
Add beets and heat thoroughly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate chip cheese cake
directions: Slice 1 package of cookies into 24 slices and place in bottom of pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over cookies.
Slice other package of cookies and place on top of cream cheese mixture. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Slice and serve.

title: quick potato salad
directions: Cut slightly cooled potatoes into 1-inch cubes.
In a large bowl, combine potatoes, onions and salad dressing; toss gently. Dust with paprika.
Garnish with bacon bits.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage until crumbly; drain.
Saute celery, onion and pepper in 1 tablespoon grease.
Cook soup mix and rice in boiling water for 7 minutes.
Mix all together and bake 1 hour at 350°. Slivered almonds may be added if desired.

title: breakfast sausage souffle
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Mix all other ingredients in bowl and add sausage.
Pour into 8 x 10-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then at 300° for 15 minutes.
Prepare ahead. Refrigerate overnight.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil; add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients; fold in grated carrots and nuts.
Bake in large flat pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pepperoni puffs
directions: Mix
flour,
milk, baking powder, egg and grated cheese until well
mixed.
Add pepperoni.
Grease small muffin tins. Fill
tins 3/4
full with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Makes 24 to 30 puffs.

title: corn dogs
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Cut in the shortening; mix the egg with the milk, then add to the other ingredients.
Roll wieners, one at a time in mixture and pan-fry in hot grease until brown.

title: icing
directions: Beat Crisco and sugar together until creamy and sugar is gone. Meanwhile, in a small pot, add flour and milk, stirring with a wire whisk constantly until it thickens.
Cool completely.
Then add everything together and beat until creamy.
Next, add vanilla and beat until fluffy.

title: 5 can casserole
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Top with crushed potato chips. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hot wine punch
directions: Bring wine and other ingredients to a boil.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Let stand briefly (about 3 to 5 minutes).
Serve in mugs with 1 cinnamon stick.
Great hot beverage for cold winter days.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach as directed.
Drain.
Place all ingredients and 1/4 of spinach in large bowl.
Blend with electric blender until mixture is partially blended.
Add remaining spinach a little at a time.
Blend until smooth about 2 minutes.
Serve in hollowed out round bread.

title: mints
directions: Mix, roll out, cut in desired shapes and dry.

title: company banana pudding
directions: Whip pudding, milk, Cool Whip and sour cream together.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with vanilla wafers.
Add 1/2 of pudding, then layer bananas.
Repeat wafers, pudding and bananas.
Refrigerate. (This can be made in 1/2 recipe for smaller family.)

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease 4 loaf pans and flour. Then fill 1/2 full and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: In a large bowl, stir together cornstarch and 1/4 cup cold water.
Add sugar, lemon juice and the blackberries; combine this mixture thoroughly.
Pour into an 8-inch skillet or baking pan (2 inches deep).
In a bowl, combine flour, remaining sugar, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Blend in butter.
Add 1/4 cup boiling water.
Stir until it forms a dough.
Bring the berry mixture to a boil on top of the stove, stirring often.
Drop tablespoons of dough into boiling mixture until all dough is used up.
Stir and bake in preheated oven at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: sausage balls
directions: Bake on 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: summer vegetable salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add dressing.
Cool at least 3 hours.

title: ken's prune jam
directions: Boil until mixture is thick.
Just delicious.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Stir apples and sugar in a bowl; let stand until juice forms. Sift flour, soda and salt; mix into apple mixture.
Beat eggs well; add oil and vanilla.
Stir well.
Bake in greased 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° until done.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: You must have the starter before you do any of the following. You get the starter from a friend, or you can make your own starter.

title: vegetable cheese soup
directions: Boil vegetables in 2 cups water until tender, about 10 minutes.
Chop into smaller pieces.
Do not drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1/2 hour or until heated thoroughly.

title: miracle cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; cool.
Add lemon juice.
Beat cream cheese well.
Add sugar; beat well.
Add vanilla and the cooled jello mixture; mix well.

title: easy party rolls
directions: Cut rolls into halves.
Place ham and cheese in between rolls. Melt butter and add all remaining ingredients.
Pour over rolls. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: almond paste cookies
directions: Put paste through a food processor.
Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into walnut size balls.
Top with 1/4 cherry. Bake on parchment paper in a 325° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool completely before removing from paper.

title: quick light rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix together with hands and place in a covered bowl in refrigerator for 3 hours.
Make into desired rolls and bake 20 minutes in hot oven.

title: best summer potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until just done (do not overcook). Cool. Slice potatoes medium thin, leaving the skins on. Combine all ingredients. Mix lightly and chill.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Cook chicken until tender in water with onion, celery, salt and pepper. Debone chicken and return to broth. Add corn. Just before serving, add eggs.

title: grandma's large chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl and mix well.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° until done in center.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Heat vinegar with sugar and salt until sugar melts.
Add celery seed and pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight before using.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar.
Stir well.
Add flour, nuts and vanilla.
Shape into balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for 20 minutes or until light brown.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs, onion and grated potatoes; beat with a spoon.
Pour oil into skillet about 1/4-inch deep and heat.
Dip 2 tablespoons batter into hot oil, cooking until golden brown.
Turn to brown other side.

title: chinese beef choufleur
directions: Cut meat into small strips; separate cauliflower into flowerets.
Brown meat in margarine about 5 minutes.
Add cauliflower, green pepper, soy sauce and garlic.
Stir lightly to coat veggies.
Cover and simmer until veggies are tender, about 10 minutes.
Blend cornstarch, sugar and broth; add to meat mixture. Cook and stir constantly until heated and sauce is thickened. Serve over rice.
Great with eggrolls!

title: sugar balls
directions: Dissolve margarine and sugar.
Add dates.
Cook until thick. Cool slightly and add 1 cup nuts and Rice Krispies cereal.
Roll in balls and then in powdered sugar.

title: apple torte
directions: Beat egg and add sugar, flour, salt and baking powder.
Add sugar mixture to apples, nuts and vanilla.
Put in 9-inch pie tin. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Top with whipped cream.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Pop popcorn and keep hot in slow oven at 250° to 350°.
Melt butter and stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring for 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in soda and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn, mixing well.
Bake in roasting pan.
Stir every 15 to 20 minutes. Cool completely and break apart.
Store in airtight container.

title: wild rice
directions: Saute all ingredients, except broth, in butter for 10 minutes. Stir in broth.
Pour into a greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: carrot pie
directions: Mix carrots, rice, cheese, onion and basil.
Spread in plate. Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender or 1 minute with beater.
Pour into plate (pie).
Bake until knife inserted comes clean, 30 to 35 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken indienne
directions: Thinly slice chicken breasts across the grain.
In a medium bowl combine chicken, ginger, cornstarch, water and salt.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pour half of the batter into cake pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: dee's baked beans
directions: Drain the baked beans.
Place in sauce pan; now add ketchup, worcestershire sauce, brown sugar, onion and bacon.
Stirring occasionally over low heat for about an hour.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Fry sausage in pan, do not drain.
Add cubed cheese and remaining ingredients.
Spoon onto slices of party rye (2 loaves). Let sit on tray until firm and place in freezer bag and freeze.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant; drain.
Cook sausage, saute onions and celery. Prepare stuffing mix according to package instructions.
Mix all together.
Bake for 20 minutes in a 325° oven.
Top with cheese. Cook until cheese is melted.

title: spinach crostini
directions: Combine all ingredients. Spread on French Bread loaf cut into 1/2 inch slices.
Bake 18 minutes or until brown in 350 degree oven.

title: crawfish casserole
directions: Saute seasoning in butter until soft.
Add tomatoes and steam 10 minutes, covered.
Cook rice according to directions.
Add soup to tomato mixture and blend in.
Combine crawfish, rice and mixture in casserole and top with 1/2 to 1 cup shredded Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until bubbly.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Combine and set aside jello and boiling water.
Using a food chopper, grind vegetables.
Combine all ingredients with jello and water in oblong container.
Refrigerate.
Serve with mayonnaise on top and with Ritz crackers.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream
oleo
and sugar; add rest of ingredients leaving raisins to last.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: garden gumbo
directions: Peel and slice tomatoes into chunks.
Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil, then simmer slowly for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan before serving.

title: versatile roast
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, onion soup mix, garlic, pepper and salt by shaking well in Reynold's brown-in-bag (be careful of steam in hot bag), coating inside as well.
Lay bag out in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish or roasting pan and distribute flour mix over bottom inside the bag.
Put prepared (cleaned and trimmed) meat in bag, turning to coat with flour mix.
Hold bag opening up from pan and add water (small roasts will need less water).
Tie and slit top.
Cook 2 to 3 hours, depending on meat tenderness.
Slice and stir up gravy before serving.

title: applesauce
directions: Quarter and wash apples, but do not peel.
Cover with water and cook until nearly tender; add salt, sugars, and butter.
Cook until very tender.
Put through strainer or in a blender and flavor with vanilla.

title: bojangle biscuits
directions: Mix all dry ingredients and cut in Crisco.
Add buttermilk and roll out dough.
Cut thick biscuits and dip biscuit into melted butter.
Place in pan and bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until blended.
Add vanilla and cream; season with nutmeg.
Mix well and chill.

title: caesar salad
directions: Crush the garlic in a small bowl; add oil and let stand several hours.

title: spice cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet in balls the size of a walnut.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Test for doneness with a toothpick, same as you would a cake.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Put in layers with cooked hamburger.
Bake at 350°.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine peanuts, sugar, corn syrup and salt into a
deep 2-quart bowl.
Microwave on High 4 minutes.
Stir well.
Microwave on High an additional 4 minutes. Add margarine and vanilla.
Stir. Microwave on High 2 1/2 minutes.
Gently stir in baking soda until light and foamy.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet.
Cool. Break into pieces
and enjoy.

title: quick and delicious beer bread
directions: Stir first three ingredients together well. Pour into 9 x 5 loaf pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes. Pour melted butter over top and bake for 10 more minutes.

title: spanish cabbage
directions: Fry bacon.
Set aside.
In small amount of bacon grease, saute onions and peppers.
Cut cabbage and put on top of onions and peppers.
Reduce heat.
Add 1/4 cup water.
Put tight lid on and let simmer for 10 minutes.
Chopped tomatoes on top.
Cover for few minutes until tomatoes get tender.
Stir together.
Salt, pepper and sugar to taste.
Crumble bacon on top when serving.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Drain and add margarine while hot.
Beat with mixer; add sugar, eggs, milk and flavoring.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake for 30 minutes longer.
Makes 2 pies.

title: peanut butter sticks
directions: Cut bread into 4 to 5 sticks.
Place on cookie sheet and toast in 250° oven until browned.
Mix peanut butter and oil in a double boiler.
Dip each bread stick in peanut butter mixture.
Coat with graham cracker crumbs.
Let cool completely.
Store in tins.

title: hungarian stew
directions: Saute onions in oil.
Add peppers; saute 1 minute.
Add tomatoes and meat.
Cover stew for 15 minutes.
Can be made a day ahead and reheated.

title: no sugar cake
directions: Place bananas, 1/2 cup chopped dates and milk in blender and puree.
Cream butter, egg yolks and rice syrup.
Sift together and add flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Mix at medium speed for 2 or 3 minutes.
Add blender mixture and mix well.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry and fold into batter.
Pour batter into three 8-inch oiled and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Frost with No Sugar Frosting.

title: miniature cheesecake
directions: Mix until smooth.
Fill each cupcake 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
When cool, top each with cherry pie filling.

title: zesty meat balls
directions: Combine everything but the sugar, vinegar, tomato juice, and worcestershire sauce in a large mixing bowl and mix well. Next shape mixture into 1 in. balls. Cook meat balls in hot oil until lightly browned and then drain. Place meat balls in a 13x9 baking dish. Combine the sugar, vinegar, tomato juice, and worcestershire sauce and pour over the meat balls.bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cashew-carrot soup
directions: Melt butter and oil in large soup pot.
Saute onions 1 minute, stir in carrots and saute until onions are soft and transparent. Stir in tomato paste, apple, stock and salt.
Bring to a boil, stir in rice and cook until soup is a beautiful orange and carrots are tender, about a half hour.
Add raisins and cashews and simmer until raisins are plump, about 5 minutes.
Add 2 1/2 cups milk and heat or chill and serve cold.
Serves 8.

title: baked rigatoni
directions: Saute onions and bell pepper in oil.
Add ground beef; brown. Drain.
Add tomato paste, water and tomatoes.
Add salt, pepper and oregano to taste.
Simmer, adding water as needed.
Cook rigatoni as directed.
Wash and drain.
Layer cooked rigatoni, sauce, Ricotta and Mozzarella until all used, ending with Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted, approximately 30 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pineapple, cherry pie filling and coconut over the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Spread dry cake mix over this. Slice butter evenly over this.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top of this. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat and pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake in 350° oven for approximately 50 minutes.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Cook bacon crispy so that it can be broken up.
Cut up onion, broccoli and cauliflower.
Add bacon and cheese.
Make dressing with red wine vinegar, salad dressing and sugar.
Pour over salad and let set 24 hours before serving.

title: skillet biscuit loaf
directions: In a 10-inch nonstick skillet over low heat, melt margarine with garlic.
Coat biscuits with Parmesan cheese, then place in skillet, overlapping slightly.
Cover; cook over low heat 8 minutes or until underside is browned.
Invert biscuits onto plate, then slide back into skillet.
Cover.
Cook 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 10 servings.

title: dear abby's cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter.
Add to graham cracker crumbs and confectioners sugar.
Line bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Pack firmly.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: In a 1-quart shallow casserole dish, combine peaches, sugar, 1 tablespoon Bisquick and cinnamon.
In a small bowl, put 2/3 cup Bisquick.
Cut in margarine until the consistency of peas.
Stir in milk and put on fruit.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: mostaccioli casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain and add sauce to noodles.
Brown beef in skillet; drain grease and add to noodles and sauce.
Stir cottage cheese and egg together and add to noodle mixture.
Sprinkle liberally with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 425°, uncovered, for 25 minutes.
Add Mozzarella cheese and bake 5 minutes more.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased casserole.
Bake in a preheated oven for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown meat, jalapeno pepper, onion, salt, pepper and garlic powder in heavy skillet.
Mix flour, corn meal and baking powder. Add egg, corn, milk, sugar and 1/2 of cheese.
Mix with meat mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350°
until done.
Then put remainder of cheese on top.
Cook until melted and bubbly.

title: shaky egg custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake at 400° in unbaked pie shell for 10 minutes; then turn oven to 350° and bake until brown.

title: shrimp surprise
directions: Combine ingredients.
Spread on party rye bread.
Great for a party.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix well (let set 12 hours).
Will keep 3 weeks.
Great with raw vegetables.

title: chicken fried steak
directions: Dip steaks in evaporated milk, then into flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Repeat once (reserve milk for later).
Fry in 1-inch hot oil over medium-high heat until golden brown or desired crispness.
Take 1/4 cup drippings, browned; mix with 1/4 cup flour.
Mix thoroughly.
Add beef consomme and rest of milk.
You may wish to use more milk for thickness of gravy you prefer.
Bring mixture to a very light boil, add sweet vermouth.
Do not salt gravy!
May wish to season with pepper.

title: crispy cucumbers
directions: Arrange cucumbers and onions in alternate layers.
Put salt on top and cover with boiling water.
Let stand 3 hours, then drain.

title: hot turkey salad casserole
directions: Mix melted butter and crumbs.
Set aside.
Mix all other ingredients, except cheese.
Place in buttered casserole.
If mixture is too dry, add can of cream of chicken soup, thinned with half can milk.
Top with cheese and sprinkle with buttered crumbs. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apricot filled bars
directions: Place apricots and undrained pineapple in saucepan.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Mix in 1/2 cup sugar and simmer 5 minutes longer; cool.

title: saucy pork chop
directions: Place butter in a shallow 1-quart casserole dish.
Microwave at High for 20 seconds, or until melted.
Add mushrooms, onion and green pepper; cover and microwave at High for 2 to 3 minutes, or until vegetables are tender, stirring once.
Stir in tomato, water, lemon juice and seasonings.
Place pork chop over mixture and spoon a small amount of vegetable mixture over pork chop.
Cover; microwave at Medium (50% power) for 8 to 10 minutes.
Turn pork chop over; cover and continue to microwave at Medium for 5 to 10 minutes, or until meat next to bone loses pink color.
Serve pork chop over rice; garnish with green pepper ring, if desired.
Yields 1 serving.

title: christmas pudding
directions: Pour milk into saucepan and scald.
Remove from heat.
Beat eggs and add sugar gradually.
Mix well.
Add milk to egg mixture, a little at a time.
Add rest of ingredients into large baking dish.
Set dish into a pan of water and place in middle of oven.

title: reuben sandwiches
directions: To chop an onion without tears, leave the root end up and cut below the roots.

title: chicken and rice(for crock-pot)
directions: Put rice over bottom of pot.
Pour water over rice.
Place chicken pieces over rice.
Pour soups over chicken, cover and cook. Heat control to 280° and cook 4 to 5 hours.

title: crawfish etouffee(a healthier way)
directions: Season crawfish tails with salt and peppers.
Set aside.

Put oil in a heavy pot. Add onions, bell pepper, garlic and celery. Cook until vegetables are soft, stirring constantly. Add tails and cook over medium heat for about 5 minutes, stirring often. Add 1 1/2 cups water. Bring to a boil and simmer for 15 minutes. Stir occasionally. Dissolve cornstarch in remaining 1/2 cup water. Add to mixture, stirring until sauce is smooth. Add green onions, parsley and Worcestershire sauce (and hot sauce, if desired). Simmer 10 minutes. Serve over hot, fluffy rice.
Serve 8.

title: salmon loaf with cucumber sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients; mix lightly. Shape into loaf in shallow baking dish.
Bake for 40 minutes. Serve with Cucumber Sauce.

title: jack mackerel cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into patties.
If too moist, add more meal; if too dry, add a little juice off mackerel. Fry in hot oil until a golden brown on both sides.

title: swiss broccoli soup
directions: Heat milk until simmering.
Cook broccoli and onions in milk until tender.
Melt butter in small saucepan.
Stir in flour, add this mixture to milk mixture.
Cook 3 minutes; remove from heat and add cheese and salt.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Serve immediately.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Partially freeze meat; thinly slice across the grain into bite-size strips.
Combine 1 tablespoon flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt; coat meat with flour mixture.
In a skillet, heat 2 tablespoons butter.
Add meat; brown quickly on both sides.
Add mushrooms, onion and garlic; cook 3 to 4 minutes or until onion is crisp-tender.
Remove meat and mushrooms mixture from pan.
Add 2 tablespoons butter to pan drippings; stir in 2 tablespoons of the flour.
Add tomato paste, bouillon granules and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Stir in 1 1/4 cups water.
Cook and stir over medium-high heat until bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes longer.
Combine sour cream and remaining 1 tablespoon flour.
Return meat and mushrooms to skillet.
Stir in sour cream mixture and wine.
Heat through, but do not boil.
Serve over noodles.
Serves 4.

title: new orleans style spaghetti
directions: Mix together and simmer until cheese melts.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: graham cracker brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread into 8-inch square greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: heart smart cocoa banana shake
directions: In covered blender at low speed, blend all ingredients about 30 seconds.
Pour into glass.
Makes 1 serving.

title: apple and cherry strudel
directions: Add vinegar to warm water.
Put flour in large mixing bowl. Add Wesson oil, dash of salt, water and vinegar combination.
Blend in KitchenAid mixer about 10 minutes.
When well blended and tender, cover and let rest for 1 hour.
Place a large sheet on table or sink top.
Roll out dough to a large circle.
Now gently place hands under dough and gently pull to cover entire sheet.
Let rest while you slice apples very thin.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over 1/3 of dough.
Place apples over crumbs; sprinkle with 1 cup sugar. Sprinkle cinnamon lightly over all apples.
Squeeze lemon juice on top of all.
Gently roll cloth until strudel is completely rolled. Place butter (melted) before you place bread crumbs.
Place on buttered cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Slice and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown ground beef in heavy kettle.
Drain excess fat and add tomato juice, onion, potatoes, carrots and salt.
Cover and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Make white sauce with butter, flour and milk.
Blend into first mixture and serve.

title: spring salad
directions: Cook noodles until tender; drain.
Add celery, onion and dressing.
Salt and pepper to your own taste.
You can add sweet peppers or boiled eggs if you like.

title: favorite cocoa fudge icing
directions: In saucepan, cook mixture until it boils and then allow it to boil for 1 to 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Let cool while cake bakes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix all ingredients. Add oats last. Pour hot water over oats. Let stand while mixing other ingredients. Bake in 9 x 13 pan for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry-pineapple jello mold
directions: Combine strawberry jello with boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add pineapple chunks, frozen strawberries and nuts. Pour half of mixture into mold/dish and set.
When set, spread sour cream, then add rest of mixture.
Chill.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Combine all except mushrooms.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Drop in mushrooms and simmer 5 minutes, stirring mushrooms occasionally.
Remove from heat and allow to cool in marinade.
Refrigerate.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Set aside 2/3 cup of cake mix.
Combine remaining cake mix, butter and beaten egg.
Stir by hand until crumbly.
Press evenly over bottom and 1-inch up sides of ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine 3 eggs, corn syrup, brown sugar and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Add the reserved cake mix.
Stir by hand until combined well.
Spread this filling evenly over baked crust and sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until filling is set.
Cool.
Cut in bars.

title: chocolate crunch brownies
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar. Add eggs. Stir in cocoa, flour, vanilla and salt. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool. Spread Marshmallow Creme over brownies.
In a small saucepan, melt peanut butter and chocolate chips. Stir constantly. Remove from heat. Stir in cereal.
Spread over marshmallow layer. Chill before cutting. Store in refrigerator.
(Peanut butter and chocolate chips can be melted in your microwave.)

title: easy beef and dumpling dinner
directions: At 7 a.m., put beef, carrots and potatoes with salt, pepper and Gravy Master into 6-quart crock-pot and cover with water. Cook on high all day.
At 4:00 p.m., remove finished beef, potatoes and carrots.
Pour liquid through strainer into 6-quart saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Add dumplings; return to boil.
Reduce heat to simmer for at least 30 minutes, stirring gently often.

title: citrus pineapple punch
directions: Pour pineapple juice concentrate into punch bowl. Add water, lemon juice and sweet orange marmalade. Stir to combine.
Add seltzer.
Add sherbet and ice cubes.
Garnish with orange slices and maraschino cherries.
Makes 6 (12 ounce) servings each.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese and mix all ingredients together.
Roll cheese ball in pecans.

title: glorified cabbage
directions: Shred and cook the cabbage until tender and drain.
Melt butter and saute onion.
Add cheese. Cook until cheese is melted. Add soup, 3/4 cup bread, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup bread over top. Cover and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Uncover and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: corn souffle
directions: Combine all ingredients in 8 x 8 dish/pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until top is light brown around the edges.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
Beat eggs.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for approximately 1 hour.

title: oven baked chicken
directions: Soak chicken in salt water for 20 minutes; dry with paper towel.
Melt butter in shallow dish.
Dip chicken in butter, roll in corn flakes crumbs and sprinkle with salt.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with foil; bake at 325° for 1 hour and 5 minutes. Remove foil and bake for another 5 minutes.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot, except evaporated milk and cheese.
Cover and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours.
Add cheese and evaporated milk in the last hour.

title: microwave oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk, and butter.
Microwave on high for 4 minutes, stirring after 2 minutes.
Add oats, peanut butter, and vanilla.
Stir until mixed well and spoon out.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Mix all soups with rice and 2/3 of dry onion soup in a large bowl.
Blend thoroughly and pour into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Place chicken pieces, skin side up, on top of mixture.
Pour remaining dry onion soup mix over chicken.
Cover pan, sealing tightly, with aluminum foil.
Bake in oven for 2 1/2 hours at 325°.
Serves 6.

title: egg benedict souffles
directions: Beat together eggs, heavy cream.
Add ham and cheese, plus dash salt.
Spoon into 6 or 7 well buttered custard cups; place in pan filled with hot water.
Bake at 275° for 35 to 45 minutes or until set.
Prepare a Hollandaise Sauce.

title: carrot salad
directions: Clean, peel and slice carrots crosswise or diagonally.
Boil in salted water until tender-crisp.
Drain and cool.
Add cut up pepper and onion.
Pour following dressing over vegetable mixture and refrigerate.

title: betty's cheshire cheese straws
directions: Sift flour and salt into bowl.
Cut butter in with pastry blender until pebbly texture.
Stir in cheese and seed.
Mix together Worcestershire sauce and 1 tablespoon of water; sprinkle liquid over flour and toss gently.
Add water until mixture clings together and forms a ball.
Roll out to 1/8-inch thick; cut into 6 to 8-inch strips.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: yellow cabbage pickles
directions: Add the salt to the cabbage and let stand overnight.
Then drain as dry as you can and cover with cold water for 15 minutes. Drain and press cabbage as dry as possible.
Make syrup of the next 6 ingredients. Let all this come to a boil and pour over cabbage.
Mix well and pack in jars; seal.

title: stuffed pork tenderloin
directions: Mix stuffing with apples and pecans.
Butterfly tenderloin. Lay Prosciutto on inside surface.
Stuff it, then roll it and tie tenderloin.
Place, seam side down, in greased pan.
Drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 425° for about 50 minutes.

title: rice and peas
directions: Place water in 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to rapid boil.
Wash the peas well under cold running water, about 2 minutes.
Place peas in boiling water.
Add salt; cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Stir in rice, onion and butter.
Stir to blend. Cover and simmer until all water is absorbed, about 2 minutes. Fluff mixture with fork.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: brown rice
directions: Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into a greased 13 x 7 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes.

title: banana flip
directions: Put ingredients into blender container; cover.
Blend on #6 speed for 20 seconds or until smooth.
Yields 1 serving.

title: pizza dough
directions: Sift together flour and salt. Add 1/2 cup lukewarm water to yeast; let stand 5 minutes. Make a hole in the flour; work in yeast mixture and remaining water. Oil hands and knead dough for 10 to 12 minutes. Cover; let rise in warm place for 2 hours. Roll out onto pizza pan. Add desired toppings. Bake at 450° for about 25 minutes.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Prepare and bake potatoes.
Cut each potato in half.
Scoop out inside of potato, leaving a thin shell.
Mash potatoes until little or no lumps remain.
Add remaining ingredients; beat until smooth.
Add 1/4 cup margarine while beating.
Spoon mixture back into shells.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage until crumbly; drain.
Spread each slice of bread with butter; cut into cubes.
Place bread cubes in a 13 x 9 x 2 inch dish.
Sprinkle with sausage and top with cheese. Combine remaining ingredients; beat well and pour over mixture. Chill 8 hours.
Remove and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: maple nut squares
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan or spray with vegetable cooking spray.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until done.

title: corn beef casserole
directions: Mix together meat, soup, milk and chopped onion and cheese. Add in alternate layers with cooked macaroni.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice green tomatoes 1/4-inch thick.
Pour boiling water over tomatoes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Beat egg and milk.
Dip tomato slices in egg batter, then in flour mixture.
Fry in oil until golden.

title: spaghetti supreme
directions: Saute onion, celery, garlic, two cheeses and mushrooms in butter until tender.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings.
Add shrimp.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Add 1 tomato sauce can of water if too thick.
Pour mixture over cooked spaghetti.

title: best-ever pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, butter and Karo in heavy saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and cool slightly. Add beaten eggs, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into pie shell and bake for 1 hour at 250°.

title: baked corn
directions: Melt shortening.
Add flour and mix well.
Add milk, bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Add corn, sugar, salt and pepper. Heat thoroughly.
Remove from heat; add well-beaten eggs and pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until corn is firm.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, stir together the egg whites, garlic, basil, salt, rosemary and red pepper.
Then stir in apples, onions and bread crumbs.
Add the turkey and mix until well combined.

title: scalloped beef and macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni, drain.
Saute onion, celery, garlic and cook beef.
In a baking casserole dish combine beef, macaroni, tomatoes, chili sauce, onion, celery, garlic, spices, flour. Stir. Sprinkle top with grated cheese and bread crumbs.

title: best friends turkey tetrazzini
directions: Mix milk, flour, salt and pepper until all lumps are dissolved.
Add butter and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to boil.
Add remaining ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Stir together and place into greased casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs and pats of butter or margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: josh and emily's garden fresh squash casserole
directions: Layer squash slices in baking dish; pour soup over squash. Sprinkle with salt and pepper; stir around covering squash. Spread cheese, then top with crumbled Ritz crackers.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
If using frozen squash, cook down in saucepan until soft, 1/2 hour on medium heat.

title: best ever pie crust
directions: Measure all ingredients into a mixing bowl.
Combine just until all ingredients
are mixed well.
Make 6 balls of dough and roll each one out individually on a floured surface.
This recipe yields 6 single or 3 double crusts.

title: hawaiian sweet potato
directions: Combine sweet potato, pineapple, orange juice and mix well.
Combine Half and Half, brown sugar and oleo, cook over low heat, stirring constantly until oleo is melted.
Add to potato mixture along with salt and cinnamon.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour into lightly greased shallow casserole dish.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 400 degrees about 10 minutes or until coconut is lightly toasted.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Peel and dice eggplant, boil eggplant until clear; drain.
Add butter, crumbs, egg and clams, including liquid from clams.
Add all to buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until browned.

title: spiced pumpkin muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375° (190°C).
Grease 12-muffin pan.
Cream together the sugar and shortening, working it until light and fluffy.
Add egg to the mixture and beat.
Add pumpkin to mixture; mix again until combined well.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and spices.
Add this dry mixture alternately with milk to the pumpkin mixture until all ingredients are stirred in. Beat well after each addition.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake on center shelf for about 25 minutes, or until done.
Makes 12 small or 10 medium muffins.

title: thai chicken fettucine salad
directions: Combine picante sauce, peanut butter, honey, orange juice, soy sauce and ginger in small saucepan.
Cook and stir over low heat until blended and smooth.
Reserve 1/4 cup.
Toss remaining sauce mixture with hot cooked fettucine.
Cook chicken in oil until browned and cooked through (about 5 minutes).
Add reserved picante sauce mixture and mix well.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Mix together in blender.
Cook on hot griddle or frying pan. A double batch will feed 4 people.

title: cherry dunk cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and place in oblong cake pan, first the pineapple, then the cherry pie mix and then the coconut. Place dry cake mix on top.
Butter top of cake mix and bake in a 325° oven until brown.

title: nashville house fried biscuits
directions: Add yeast to warm water.
Add other ingredients and let dough rise.
Work into biscuits and drop in hot fat.

title: scottish scones
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; stir well.
Cut in butter with pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
Stir in currants.
Combine sour cream and egg yolk, stirring well; add to flour mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Let set for 24 hours before serving.
Garnish with nuts and cherries when ready to serve.

title: sweet potato angel biscuits
directions: Wash sweet potatoes; bake at 375° for 1 hour or until done. Let potatoes cool to touch; peel and mash.
Set aside 3 cups and keep warm.
Combine yeast and warm water in a 2 cup liquid measuring cup; let stand 5 minutes.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients in a large bowl; cut in shortening with a pastry blender or fork until mixture is crumbly.

Add yeast mixture and sweet potatoes, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened. Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface; knead 5 minutes. Place dough in a lightly greased bowl; cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with 2-inch round cutter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet; cover and let rise in a warm place 20 minutes or until double in bulk.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yield:
7 dozen.

title: buffet potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Hold back half of cheese.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and sprinkle rest of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bark candy
directions: Place bark in Pyrex dish.
Heat in microwave for 2 1/2 minutes on High heat until melted.
Then add peanut butter, Rice Krispies, marshmallows and peanuts.
Stir and spoon out on wax paper.

title: pineapple-cottage cheese salad
directions: Drain pineapple and measure juice.
Usually one cup of juice is drained.
Measure enough water to make a total of 2 1/2 cups with juice.
Heat water to boiling and dissolve Jell-O and salt in hot water.
Add pineapple juice.
Refrigerate until the consistency of egg white.
Add pineapple, cottage cheese, mayonnaise and nuts.
Return to refrigerator.

title: royal fudge
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa in a saucepan.
Add milk; stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved, then bring to a boil.
Stir occasionally and cook until a small amount of candy dropped in cold water forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Do not stir.
Allow to cool for 15 minutes, then beat until mixture thickens.
Stir in nuts and quickly pour into a buttered pan.

title: rotel dip
directions: Melt Velveeta cheese in microwave.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Stir until mixed well.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: tuna salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve as side dish or on bread. Serves 6.
50 calories per serving.
Fat gr. 8. 14% fat.

title: cappuccino swirl cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla in large bowl with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended. Add eggs. Mix until well blended. Stir cinnamon into 1 cup of batter in a small bowl. Stir instant coffee into remaining batter and pour into crust. Spoon cinnamon batter over coffee batter. Swirl with knife to marbleize. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until center is almost set. Cool completely on wire rack. Refrigerate at least 3 hours or overnight. Serves 8.

title: pumpkin cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In large bowl with mixer on medium speed, beat cream cheese, sugar, flour, cinnamon, ginger, salt and nutmeg. Add pumpkin, flour and evaporated milk until well blended. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake for 30 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Mix all ingredients in a 9x12x2 inch dish.
Bake in oven for 1 hour.
Serves 10.

title: cajun potato salad
directions: Peel and boil potatoes; let cool.
Boil eggs; let cool. Combine potatoes and eggs, then add remaining ingredients.
Keep in refrigerator until served.

title: casey's vinegar pie
directions: Bring sugar, water and vinegar to boiling.
Stir in butter until melted.
Mix flour with a little cold water until smooth. Add to boiling liquid slowly and stir until thickened.
Allow to cool slightly.
Pour into shell.
Cover top lattice-fashion with pastry strips.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes; reduce to 350° and bake about 25 minutes.

title: rolls
directions: Put milk, Crisco and sugar on stove and bring to boil.
Let cool until lukewarm.
Add yeast.
Put in enough flour to be like biscuit dough.
Let rise until double in size, then work down with more flour.
Roll out and let rise before cooking.

title: tuna-broccoli casserole
directions: In large Dutch oven, melt Crisco over medium heat.
Add milk; cook until bubbly.
In separate pot, cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain broccoli; drain tuna.
Mix broccoli and tuna with milk.
Pour in casserole dish.
Sprinkle seasonings on top.
Top with biscuits.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake for 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
Makes 2 bread pans (greased).

title: quick pineapple pie(sugar-free)
directions: Mix the dry pudding, pineapple and sour cream together and pour in baked pie shell.
Chill 4 hours.

title: frosted grapes
directions: Wash grapes; let dry.
Beat egg white and water until frothy. Dip grapes in egg white.
Let drip and coat with sugar.
Great for parties!

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl blend cake mix, sour cream, oil, sugar, water and eggs.
Beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Pour batter into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool and remove from pan.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put rice in 13 1/2 x 9-inch pan or glass dish.
Lay breasts on rice.
Pour melted margarine over and sprinkle soup all over. Pour water in the corners.
Cover with foil.
Bake 2 hours at 325°.

title: chicken pie
directions: Remove chicken from bones and place chicken in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix chicken broth and soup together.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Mix Bisquick and milk.
Pour over chicken and soup mixture.
Top with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers; cut into strips.
Combine cucumbers, onions, peppers and salt.
Mix with 1 quart of crushed ice.
Let stand for 3 hours, drain.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables.
Put all ingredients in a big pot and bring to a boil. Pack in jars and seal at once.

title: seafood bisque
directions: Blend soups with milk. Heat and add crab meat, shrimp and sherry just before serving.
Add a twist of lemon peel to each bowl of soup.
Serves 6.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients, except the Cool Whip, together. Fold in the Cool Whip. Pour into the crust.
Freeze until firm.

title: carrot loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a casserole dish at 350° until firm.

title: bacon & wienie's
directions: Heat oven to 325° to 350°.
Cut bacon into approximately 2 inch strips.
Wrap bacon around weinie's and put toothpick thru. Sprinkle brown sugar over top.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Layer zucchini, onion and tomatoes.
Top with sour cream. Layer zucchini, onion and tomatoes.
Mix bread crumbs with butter; sprinkle on top.
Spread with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: onion pie
directions: Heat oven at 350.

title: pizza cookie
directions: Line 12-inch pizza pan with heavy aluminum foil, grease foil, and set aside.
Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of electric mixer.
Add egg and mix well.
Combine flour and next three ingredients. Add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Stir in 1/2 the chocolate pieces and 1/4 of the chopped pecans.
Spoon batter onto prepared pan, spreading to within one inch of edge.
Sprinkle with coconut and remaining 1/4 pecans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes. Sprinkle with marshmallows and remaining 1/4 cup chocolate pieces on top.
Bake an additional five to seven minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
To serve, cut into wedges.

title: crab dip
directions: Marinate crab meat in lemon juice for 1 hour; drain.
Combine cream cheese and cream in mixer bowl; mix until smooth.
Beat in mayonnaise.
Add garlic, onions and salt; blend well.
Fold crab into sauce.
Add Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco.
Serve hot in chafing dish.
May also be served cold.
Yield: 20 servings.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Thaw broccoli, mix all ingredients.
Grease pan (9 x 13-inch), bake at 400° for 35 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: filled graham cracker cookies
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Line pan with whole graham crackers and set aside. Mix brown sugar, milk and oleo, coconut and graham cracker crumbs in a saucepan and boil 10 minutes, stirring constantly. Spread mixture over Whole Graham Crackers. Place another layer of whole graham crackers on top of filling. Frost.

title: gina's new potatoes
directions: Boil halved potatoes until they are almost fully cooked.
In a frying pan, heat oil and place potatoes, faced down, and add garlic.
Add salt, pepper and Italian blend.
Turn occasionally; cook until golden brown.

title: strawberry and sour cream squares
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add strawberries, stirring occasionally, until thawed.
Add pineapple and bananas.
Pour 1/2 mixture in casserole.
Chill until firm.
Spoon 1/2 of sour cream over jello.
Spread remaining jello on top of sour cream.
Chill. Spread remaining sour cream on top and chill.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Blend together.
Marinate meat (pork chops or chicken) for approximately 3 hours.
Cook meat on grill until done.
Baste with sauce while cooking.

title: starlight mint surprise cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients, except candy wafers and walnuts, in large mixer bowl.
Mix at lowest speed of mixer until dough forms.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Place zucchini in colander; let drain 1 hour.
In a large bowl, with a wire whisk, beat the eggs until they're frothy.
Add remaining ingredients; whisk until blended.
Stir in the zucchini, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.

title: coconut delight
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan; press mixture of graham cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle coconut and milk and top with nuts. Bake at 350° until milk turns brown.

title: squash pie
directions: Peel squash, remove seeds, cut in pieces.
Boil in salt water, add butter	and
sugar until soft.	Beat in mixer well, remove beater and	rinse
under water to wash out any strings. Add butter and
sugar,
beat again until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, then
add
milk,
nutmeg,
cinnamon,
orange peel, vanilla and lemon extract.
Bake in crust at 350° until brown. (Bake on cookie sheet
if preferred.) Add 1 small box raisins for variety.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, corn syrup, salt, vanilla and butter with rotary beater.
Mix in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt oleo in pan.
Saute onions; add soup and juice from mushrooms.
Blend together.
Pour over cooked rice in casserole. Add layer of cheese, drained mushrooms and almonds.
Bake at 350° until heated through.

title: quicky sticky buns
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl combine 2 tablespoons of the brown sugar, the corn syrup, pecans and 1 tablespoon of the margarine.
Spoon about 2 teaspoons mixture into each of 9 (2 1/2-inch) muffin pan cups.
Unroll entire crescent roll dough. Pinch seams together to form 1 rectangle.
Combine remaining 1 tablespoon brown sugar and the cinnamon.
Spread dough with remaining 1 tablespoon margarine; sprinkle with cinnamon mixture. Roll up from short ends.
Cut into 9 slices.
Place one slice in each prepared muffin pan cup.
Bake 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately invert pan onto cookie sheet or tray; cool 10 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole(or any meal)
directions: Fry sausage until cooked; drain very well on paper towels. Butter one side of bread and place evenly in bottom of a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cheese evenly over bread.
Combine beaten eggs with milk, salt and dry mustard. Pour over cheese and bread.
Sprinkle sausage on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, bake, covered, at 325° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.
Serve.

title: frozen cranberry pineapple salad
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Let stand 30 minutes until sugar dissolves.
Stir marshmallows into cranberry mixture.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon into an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan lined with plastic wrap.
Re-cover and freeze at least 8 hours. Remove from pan.
Cut into slices.
Yields 8 servings.

title: sour cream chicken breasts
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Coat chicken with crumbs; dip in mayonnaise mixture.
Place in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add pineapple.
Add grated cheese. Pour into flat, buttered baking dish.
Cover top with bread crumbs. Pour a little melted butter or margarine over the top.
Bake in a 350° oven about 40 minutes until brown on top.

title: butter clams parmesan
directions: Grind clams.
Mix all ingredients into a paste.
Spoon into clean clam shells.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and butter. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Broil until brown.

title: festive egg square
directions: Layer the first 5 ingredients.
Beat rest of ingredients together.
Pour over the layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pistachio pudding torte
directions: Wash rice.
In a large pot (nonstick), mix rice, milk, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Let come to a boil, stirring occasionally. Turn down flame to simmer.
Let simmer 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: chili con carne
directions: Cook together the hamburger, onion, celery and seasoning, about 1 hour.
Drain off fat.
Add flour, tomatoes and baked beans.
Heat through and serve.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: caramel corn
directions: Butter and salt popped corn.
Boil sugar, molasses, water, vinegar and butter to hard ball stage and add soda and stir well. Add vanilla.
Stir well.
Pour over corn and mix well.
Shape into balls or leave as is.

title: condensed milk
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and process until smooth.
Will keep several weeks in refrigerator.
Thickens as it cools.
May be frozen.
Makes about 14 ounces, about the same as a can.

title: battered "yankee" crabs
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Batter should have consistency of pancake batter.
Dip each crab in batter and cover crab.
Fry crab in 1-inch of hot oil until brown and done.
Drain and enjoy Yankee "style".
Batter can be used for deshelled shrimp and crawfish tails.
Add extra Old Bay for spicier taste.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 2-quart casserole dish. Mix sugar, flour, milk and salt. Pour mixture over melted butter. Pour fruit over batter. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Spread mixture on a 12-inch platter.
Top with picante sauce.
Top with shredded lettuce.
Top with shredded cheese.
Top with sliced black olives, if desired.
Use chips to dip.

title: pistachio sour cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cake mix, pudding, eggs, sour cream and water.
Blend to moisten.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into well-greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: chewy chocolate squares
directions: Butter square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inch.
Heat margarine and marshmallows in 3-quart saucepan, over low heat, stirring constantly, until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate chips until smooth.
Quickly stir in cereal until evenly coated. Press in pan with buttered spatula.
Cool; cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes 16 squares.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Brown
ground
beef, onion and pepper.	Drain fat.
Add chili, ketchup
and
mustard.
Simmer
10 minutes.
Pour beef mixture in casserole dish and mix in pork and beans.
Place in oven at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chili sauce
directions: Peel and chop tomatoes and onion and mix well with chopped pepper, spices and remaining ingredients.
Pour in shallow pan. Place in oven and cook for 45 minutes at 350°.
Pour into sterilized containers.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Place, in saucepan, milk, sugar, butter and cocoa; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Take off fire, add peanut butter and stir until dissolved.
Add vanilla and oatmeal.
Mix well.
Drop on wax paper.

title: sour cream rolls
directions: Put margarine in small pan and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar and cream; let set.
Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Stir in sour cream mixture.
Then mix flour and salt; gradually add to yeast and sour cream mixture and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or 8 hours.

title: rice lasagna
directions: Saute hamburger until meat is done.
Drain.
In a glass casserole dish spoon the cooked rice evenly on the ungreased bottom.
Crumble the drained hamburger on top.
With a teaspoon, place sour cream in plops randomly across other ingredients to suit individual taste.
Gently pour spaghetti sauce over all ingredients.
Top with 2 cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: pizza bites
directions: Filling:
In a bowl, combine Mozzarella cheese, sausage and pizza sauce.
Set aside.

title: souper meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in microwave tube pan or other appropriate size microwave-safe dish.
Microwave, uncovered, on High power for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and cover with wax paper; let stand 10 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix 1/2 package taco seasoning with salad dressing and set aside.
To assemble:
A few hours before serving, mix lettuce, tomatoes, beef, onions, beans and cheese into a large bowl.
Pour dressing mixture over the salad and mix.
Immediately before serving, add crushed Doritos chips and serve (or can omit if desired).

title: pie crust
directions: Combine
dry
ingredients.
Cut
in
shortening
until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Divide into 5 equal parts.	Shape into a ball; wrap and chill. May be	stored in refrigerator for several days or put in pans and freeze for later use.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine flour, baking powder and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Melt butter; remove from heat. Stir in sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Stir dry ingredients and walnuts into sugar mixture.
Spread in pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut while warm.

title: lemon custard pudding cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, butter and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Beat egg yolks. Add to mixing bowl along with milk and lemon peel.
Mix well.
Add lemon juice.
In another bowl, beat egg whites until stiff, slowly adding remaining 1/2 cup sugar while beating.
Fold into batter.
Pour into a greased 2-quart baking dish or individual ramekins.
Place in shallow pan of hot water and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes, or until lightly browned. Serve warm or chilled with confectioners sugar on top. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix lightly and refrigerate several hours.

title: zucchini vegetable pie
directions: Line bottom of greased 9-inch pie plate with 10 crackers. Stand remaining crackers around edge.
Sprinkle bottom with cheese.
In skillet, saute mushrooms, zucchini, pepper, scallions and garlic in margarine until tender.
Spread vegetable in plate. Combine remaining ingredients; pour over vegetable mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until set.
Tent crackers along edge with foil to prevent overbrowning.
Makes 6 servings.

title: macadamia cheese biscuits
directions: Sift flour with salt.
Blend butter, cheese and egg.
Gradually work in flour and nuts.
Mold into roll 1 1/2-inch diameter.
Wrap in wax paper and chill until firm.
Slice into 1/4-inch discs. Bake on lightly floured baking sheet for 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: party pizza
directions: Cook sausage.
Don't drain.
Add other ingredients.
Spread on rye bread.
May be frozen until needed.
Bake in 350°
oven for 15 minutes until brown.

title: chicken soup
directions: Cut fillets the size for serving and dip in 2 beaten eggs, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Roll in Ritz cracker crumbs.
Place in frypan with melted shortening (1/2 cup).
Cook and brown on both sides for about 1/2 hour.

title: dip
directions: Mix ingredients together and let stand overnight.
Cut center from bread to serve dip in center.
Tear up bread pieces to use in dip.

title: family's choice salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into bottle or jar and shake well.
Refrigerate.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix by hand in order given.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk (regular milk with 1/4 teaspoon vinegar).
Mash bananas and add. Pour into greased and floured pans (3 small).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: buckeyes
directions: Let butter
soften
at	room
temperature.
Mix
peanut butter, butter and	powdered sugar in a large bowl.
Roll into 1/2 inch balls.
Put
toothpicks
in
the center of each ball. Put into refrigerator until cookies are firm.

title: orange raisin cake
directions: Combine mix and sugar.
Add enough water to orange juice to measure 1 cup of liquid.
Mix liquid and eggs together.
Stir 1 cup of egg mixture into mix; beat for 2 minutes.
Add remaining liquid, raisins and orange peel.
Beat for 1 minute longer.
Pour into 2 wax paper-lined, 8-inch square pans.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Frost as desired.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Crush Ritz crackers until they are crushed fine. Pour melted butter on crackers in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.
Let cool.

title: gooey apple pie cake
directions: Prepare cake; put into 2 round pans.
Bake.
Cool.
Mix pudding according to directions.
Place cake layer on bottom of large punch bowl.
Pour pudding mixture over 1st layer (1/2 of mixture).
Add 2nd layer.
Top with apple filling, Cool Whip and nuts.
Let cool.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Mix peaches, lemon juice and water.
Let stand together 1 1/2 hours or until you can pour off 1 cup of juice.
Cook the 1 cup of peach syrup with cornstarch until thickened and clear.
It will be very thick.
Add the butter and almond extract.
Mix with peaches once it has cooled.
Pour into pie crust and chill.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream for serving.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground chuck and crumble meat up.
Add chili seasoning, Sloppy Joes seasoning and spaghetti sauce mix.
Stir this into meat.
Add spaghetti sauce and water.
Simmer until it is as thick as you want.

title: lemon pudding dessert
directions: In a bowl, cut butter into the flour until crumbly.
Press into an ungreased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 22 minutes or until set.
Let cool.
In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Fold in 1 cup whipped topping.
Spread over crust.
In a mixing bowl, beat milk and pudding mix for approximately 2 minutes.
Carefully spread over cream cheese layer.
Top with remaining whipped topping.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Beat eggs with margarine. Add rest of ingredients, except cheese. Put in buttered casserole. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes (until set). Sprinkle cheese on top. Serves 8.

title: bubble cake
directions: Combine sugar, cinnamon and brown sugar.
Thaw bread dough. Break small pieces of dough (about the size of golf balls.)
Roll in melted margarine, then in sugar/cinnamon mixture.
Drop in greased Bundt pan.
May sprinkle chopped nuts between layers. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Take out of refrigerator 30 minutes before baking.
Then bake 30 minutes at 350°; turn cake upside down onto plate and pull apart.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and shortening, then add dry ingredients.
Add apples and nuts. Put in loaf pan.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then at 375° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate-chocolate chunk cookies
directions: In a double boiler over simmering water, melt the unsweetened chocolate.
Allow to cool to room temperature.
In a large bowl, combine butter, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Beat until fluffy.
Beat in egg and baking soda.
Stir in cooled chocolate and flour.
Stir in the chopped chocolate.
Transfer to small bowl and refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease baking sheet.
Use 2 to 3 tablespoons of dough (golf ball size) for each cookie and shape into ball.
Only bake 5 or 6 cookies at a time. Bake 12 minutes.
Do not overbake!
Cool on cookie sheet for 2 minutes, then transfer to paper towel for 2 minutes, then transfer to a rack to cool.
(Cool sheets between batches.)

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Cook egg, vinegar, pineapple juice, flour and sugar over low flame in a saucepan.
Combine with pineapple, apples, nuts and Cool Whip.
Enjoy.

title: easy bake cheesecake
directions: Combine sugar, cream cheese, lemon juice, salt and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Begin to blend ingredients together.
Beat eggs into mixture, one at a time.
Pour mixture into unbaked graham cracker crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Chill before serving. Garnish with your favorite fruit topping.
Serves 8.

title: party rice
directions: Stir all ingredients (except Parmesan cheese) in 11 x 13 baking dish. Sprinkle with little Parmesan cheese to taste. Bake in 350° oven 40 minutes, covered with aluminum foil. Uncover and bake 20 minutes longer.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Use on your favorite meat.

title: coconut bon bons
directions: Mix well and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.
Make into small balls. Melt 3/4 c. wax and 1 bag of chocolate chips in a double boiler. Dip balls in chocolate and put on wax paper till done.
Place in covered bowl.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Mix potatoes, Velveeta cheese, mayonnaise, onion and salt and pepper to taste well.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with bacon (can use more, if desired).
Cover with olives.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour.

title: upside-down blueberry pancakes
directions: Melt butter in pie plate.
Put in berries; pour batter over top.
Bake for 18 minutes at 350°.
Loosen edges and invert.

title: sweet potato-cashew bake
directions: Combine brown sugar, cashews, salt and cinnamon.
In a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish, layer half the sweet potatoes, half the peach slices and half the brown sugar mixture.
Repeat layers. Dot with butter or margarine.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake mixture about 10 minutes longer.
Spoon brown sugar syrup over before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: lower fat spaghetti pie
directions: Cook and drain pasta; remove 1 cup.
Toss rest with Parmesan cheese and egg whites.
Turn into sprayed 10-inch pie plate and press to form crust.
Spread cottage cheese on top.
Brown hamburger and drain well.
Stir in 1 cup spaghetti and spaghetti sauce.
Spoon meat over cottage cheese.
Top with onions, peppers and mushrooms, as desired.
Cover loosely with greased foil and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake 10 minutes longer, uncovered.

title: lasagne
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown beef with onion.
Add mushrooms and garlic in large skillet.
Add whole tomatoes, tomato paste, parsley and oregano, then add salt, pepper, sugar and basil. Simmer until it thickens; stir occasionally.
Cook lasagne noodles according to the package directions.
Beat egg in bowl.
Stir in Ricotta and cottage cheeses and 1/2 teaspoon of salt.
Arrange 1/2 the noodles in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread with the cheese mixture. Cover with 1/2 of the meat sauce, then 1/2 of the Mozzarella. Repeat layers.
Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes.
Let stand before serving.

title: bread spreads
directions: Beat oleo with electric mixer, adding buttermilk gradually until light and fluffy, tastes like fresh churned butter.

title: ranch style potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes into a baking dish.
Top with dots of margarine, salt, pepper and dry dressing mix. Bake covered for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy cream puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Heat water and margarine to boil.
Stir in flour; remove from heat and beat in eggs, one at a time, until smooth.
Drop by scant 1/4 cupfuls about 2 inches apart onto greased baking sheet.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until puffs are golden brown.
Cut off tops with sharp knife and scoop out middle. Save tops.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar well. Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix soda into sour cream. Alternating, add sour cream and sifted flour while mixing.
Add flavorings and mix slightly. Grease and flour tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple swirl cake
directions: Peel, core, and cut apples into small pieces.
Mix together with 3 tablespoons of sugar and cinnamon.
Set aside.

title: chocolate oat drops
directions: Put sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk into saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Take off burner and add 1/2 cup peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Mix well; drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper.
They are ready when they harden.

title: pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch Teflon-coated loaf pan.
In small bowl, stir flour, lemon peel, baking powder and salt to mix.
Set aside.
Cream remaining ingredients.
Pour in pan.
Bake 45 minutes or until done.

title: the best green tomato catsup
directions: Mix together and simmer 20 minutes.
Pack in sterilized jars and seal.
Process 30 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: hamburger skillet supper
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add tomatoes, barbecue sauce, pepper, onions, rice and water. Bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat.
Cook at medium heat, simmer for 25 minutes.
Place cheese on top and set off stove to melt.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix all together and spread in dish so it is about 1/2-inch thick. Top with layer of lettuce, tomatoes, bell pepper, black olives, grated cheese or any of your other favorite taco toppings. Serve with favorite corn chips.

title: easy orange glazed pork roast
directions: Combine seasoning blend from 1 package of Bag'N Season for pork chops with marmalade.
Arrange cooking bag in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Spread marmalade mixture over roast.
Place roast in bag.
Close and tie.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes per pound.
Let stand 5 minutes and serve.

title: fennel au gratin
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Butter a 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Blanch the fennel for 12 to 15 minutes and drain.
Arrange cut side up in the baking dish.
Season to taste and pour the chicken broth over.
Sprinkle with the cheese.
Dot with butter and bake in the upper third of the oven for half an hour or until the top is golden.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken; cut into bite-size chunks.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Place broccoli in bottom of 1 1/2 quart shallow baking dish.
Cover broccoli with chicken.
Cover with American cheese. Mix milk and soup.
Pour over casserole.
Bake at 375° until bubbly.
Sprinkle onion rings over top; return to oven for 1 to 2 minutes.

title: cincinnati chili
directions: In a 4-quart saucepot, add ground beef and water.
Stir until beef separates to a fine texture.
Boil for 1/2 hour.
Add all ingredients and bring to a boil, uncovered.
Stir to blend.
Reduce heat and simmer, still uncovered, for 3 hours.
During last hour, pot may be covered, if it has reached desired consistency.
Makes 8 servings.

title: oven chicken(ny version)
directions: Slice chicken into chunks.
Place in large greased shallow casserole.
Mix soups with sour cream and pour over chicken.
Dot with pimento pieces.
Prepare dressing (follow directions on package).
Spread over top of cream mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Spread into buttered baking pan.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl combine all ingredients listed above in the order that they appear.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: old fashioned banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter, add eggs and beat until lemony. Mix sour milk together with baking soda in a cup, until foamy. Add to creamed mixture. Stir in salt and flour, fold in bananas. Bake in greased and floured loaf pans at 350° for 45 minutes. Makes 2 small loaves.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except cucumbers, mixing until well blended.
Stir in cucumbers.
Chill several hours or overnight. Serve with chips or vegetable dippers.
Yield: 1 2/3 cups.

title: ox tail soup
directions: Wash the ox tail well and split in small joints.
Melt the butter in a saucepan; add pieces of tail and when beginning to brown, add the chopped onion.
Fry until the onion is a deep gold, then add stock, carrot and celery (cut in thin slices), thyme, parsley and bay leaf (tied securely together), finely chopped tomatoes and claret.
Season with Worcestershire sauce, peppercorns and salt.
Let it boil.
Serve.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together, saving enough beef to roll cheese ball in.
Shape and roll in beef.
Serve with a variety of crackers.

title: black bean soup 2
directions: Wash and clean beans; soak overnight.
In morning, sort beans carefully and put in stock pot with 3 quarts water.
Add salt pork, beef, carrot, onions, cloves, mace and red pepper.
Cover and cook slowly 3 hours or until beans are very soft.
Rub through sieve.
Place hot bean liquid and puree in a tureen.
Add egg slices, lemon slices and sherry.

title: chocolate mousse
