directions: Melt the chocolate in the liqueur over very low heat and set aside.
Combine eggs + extra yolks, vanilla and sugar in container of blender and blend for 2 minutes.
Add cream and blend for another minute.
Add the chocolate mixture and blend until smooth. The mousse must be made at least three hours ahead and chilled thoroughly.
It will keep for several days in the refrigerator and for months in the freezer.
If frozen, thaw in the refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours.

title: valerie's lemon chicken
directions: In a bowl, marinate first 4 ingredients for 15 minutes.
In another bowl, mix next 3 ingredients for batter.
Heat 2 cups oil in deep frying pan.
Dip chicken in batter mix and fry in oil until a rich golden brown or until chicken is completely cooked. Remove and slice into 1/2-inch strips.
Keep warm in oven.
Slice lemons thin and remove seeds.

title: easy sausage-potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes until just tender; drain.
Saute smoked sausage and onion; drain.
Mix together potatoes, sausage, onion, Cheez Whiz and sour cream.
Pour mixture into a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening and then eggs. Add peanut butter and vanilla. Sift flour and baking soda and add. Roll in small balls. Flatten with fork. Bake at 325° for approximately 13 to 14 minutes.

title: cucumber-yogurt salad
directions: With vegetable peeler, remove several lengthwise strips of peel from each cucumber.
Halve cucumbers lengthwise and scrape out seeds; thinly slice.
Place cucumbers in medium bowl; stir in next 7 ingredients.
Serve cucumber salad on lettuce; garnish with lemon.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Fresh broccoli gives the best taste.

title: chicken salad delight
directions: Toss and chill.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.
Recipe from Hills and Pines Garden Club, Raleigh, North Carolina.

title: mother's broccoli casserole
directions: Cook until barley tender in salted water and broccoli.
Drain well and place in shallow casserole.

title: jalapeno pie
directions: Place sliced peppers in a single layer in pie pan, 1/2 to 3/4 inch apart.
Mound grated cheese over jalapenos (like a mountain peak).
Beat eggs thoroughly.
Pour slowly over mound of cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until top of pie begins to brown.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Cook rhubarb, sugar and pineapple 30 minutes, stirring often. Remove from heat.
Stir in Jell-O.
Can and seal.

title: glorious morning muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients. Stir in honey, sugar, eggs and oil. Add the vanilla and orange juice.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring just until mixed. Grease or paper 12 cup muffin tins. Fill 3/4 full.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes. Cool on rack.
Yields 24.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; blend well.
Roll into 1 or 1 1/2-inch balls.
Refrigerate overnight.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in top of double boiler over boiling water.
Dip each ball in melted chocolate and place on waxed paper until cool.
Put in covered container.
Yield:
60 to 75 pieces.

title: golden cream soup
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients. Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Sprinkle flour over cold milk and shake gradually.
Add to hot mixture, stirring, until it thickens. Remove from heat and add cheese.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into casserole dish. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top and bake for 45 minutes at 400°.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Melt butter and mix remaining ingredients. Pour into buttered casserole and refrigerate. Cut into squares.

title: magic lemon meringue pie
directions: In medium size bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk, lemon juice and rind.
Blend in egg yolks.
Turn into cooled crust.

title: lamb stew
directions: Brown lamb and garlic in hot oil.
Add sherry and enough water to barely cover lamb, bay leaf, basil, oregano, pepper and allspice.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add rest of ingredients, except cornstarch and water, and simmer until vegetables are tender.
If stew needs thickening, combine 2 tablespoons cornstarch with 2 tablespoons water and add to stew while stirring.
This recipe can also be used for beef stew.

title: spicy garlic chicken with mushrooms
directions: Place chicken in a medium bowl.
Add egg white, 1 tablespoon cornstarch, 1 tablespoon soy sauce and 2 tablespoons cold water. Toss to coat.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator 1 hour.

title: super seafood salad
directions: Cut Crab Delights in half or shred with electric mixer on low speed.
Combine with mayonnaise, celery and onion.
Makes 4 servings.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix in bowl and pour into 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: corn chowder
directions: Saute onion in 4 tablespoons of butter until tender.
Add corn, potato, chicken broth and herbs.
Simmer 25 minutes.
Puree soup in blender.
Return to pot.
Add cream, 6 tablespoons of butter, salt and pepper.
Serve hot.

title: corn pudding
directions: Stir flour, salt, sugar and butter into corn. Beat eggs.
Add to milk, then to corn.
Bake in a large greased casserole at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into small balls.
Put on a cookie sheet and freeze.
Put frozen balls in a plastic bag and store in freezer.

title: lemon iced ambrosia bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine flour and confectioners sugar.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Press into bottom of lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal cinnamon drops
directions: I usually double the recipe.
Mix all the ingredients together.
Drop spoonfuls onto cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: deer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into 3 logs.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Saute mushrooms and green pepper in butter.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Cook over low heat and stir until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Slowly stir in broth and milk.
Bring to a boil over low heat, stirring constantly.
Boil one minute.
Add chicken and pimento.
Cook until meat is cooked through.
Serve over biscuits, rice or noodles.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Use cornmeal mix according to directions, using less milk and adding can of creamed corn.
Brown meat.
Add onion and peppers. Simmer until tender.

title: mexican chicken salad
directions: Mix mayo, picante sauce, garlic and chili powder in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix lightly.
Serve with tortillas, 6 servings.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook small beets.
Skin and pack in clean tight jars.
Pour hot syrup over beets and seal at once.

title: cranberry marshmallow salad
directions: In a large bowl mix the chopped cranberries, sugar and pineapple together. Let sit for 1/2 hour. Add marshmallows and whipped cream. Mix well and refrigerate before serving. Add 1/2 c. walnuts if desired.

title: chile 'n' cheese breakfast casserole
directions: Spread cut side of each English muffin with 1 teaspoon butter and place, buttered side down, in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cook sausage in skillet until browned, stirring to crumble; drain.
Layer half each of sausage, chiles and cheese over English muffin.
Combine sour cream and eggs; pour over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook noodles and brown ground beef. Pour noodles in pan, mix sour cream and cream cheese and pour over noodles, then mix ground beef with sauce and pour over noodles.
Cover top of casserole with shredded cheese.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: six flavor pound cake
directions: Mix butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well one at a time.
Add flour, sifted 3 times.
Add milk; mix well.
Add all extracts; mix well.
Last, add baking powder; mix well.
Start in cold oven at 325°; bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: eggs souffle
directions: Crumble bacon on top (optional).
Butter all slices of bread and cut into cubes.
Lay in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper; pour over bread. Cube cheese and throw over it. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put the first 4 ingredients in a glass dish in microwave for 4 minutes on High. Stir.
Put back in for 4 more minutes on High. Take out and add the vanilla and margarine.
Put back in for 2 minutes on High. Stir. Add the baking soda.
Pour on greased cookie sheet.
Makes half cookie sheet.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Half cook broccoli; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake uncovered in 300° oven for 30 minutes to 1 hour until lightly browned and most of the liquid is absorbed.
Let stand about five minutes.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

Put in the pan the undrained pineapple, blueberries with 3/4 cup sugar sprinkled over, cake mix poured over these ingredients, melted margarine poured over cake mix, 1/4 cup sugar sprinkled over mix and pecans chopped and sprinkled on top.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in cake pan; put pineapple in pan, then add brown sugar over pineapple.
Then mix cake mix as told on box; put cake batter in cake pan.
Cook 35 to 45 minutes at 350° until done. Turn pan over on cake plate.

title: pickled beets
directions: Drain beets, reserving liquid in saucepan. Add sugar, vinegar and cinnamon sticks to reserved liquid.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Pour over beets; cool.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.

title: rice delight(microwave)
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, heat butter 1 to 2 minutes on High until melted.
Stir in rice; heat 5 minutes on High, until rice is browned.
Stir once.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat, covered, for 8 minutes on High.
Continue cooking on Defrost an additional 11 minutes, until rice is tender.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften.
In a mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, yogurt and vanilla.
Add sugar.
Mix well.
Refrigerate; the mixture will thicken.
Serve with sliced strawberries, apples, pears and bananas.
May add few drops of food coloring to dip to coordinate with fruit.

title: chocolate crunchy cluster
directions: In a saucepan or microwave melt chips with milk. In a large mixing bowl combine noodles and nuts, stir in chocolate mixture. Scoop tablespoon size portion and drop onto wax paper-lined baking sheet.
Chill for 2 hours or until firm.
Store loosely covered in cool dry place.
Use within 2 days.
Makes 4 dozen clusters.

title: raisin pie
directions: Boil raisins in water until soft.
Mix sugar and flour.
Add this to raisins and water and heat until it thickens, then add margarine.
Pour into pie crust and cover with other crust. Sprinkle lightly with sugar and brush with cream or margarine. Bake at 350° until brown, about 45 minutes.

title: recipe to be a good neighbor
directions: Blend all together, form into one being and serve generous portions daily to everyone you meet.

title: no bake bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add milk, sugar and vanilla.
Heat this mixture to boiling point, but don't let it boil!
Have a bowl of coarsely broken bread ready.
(Good way to use older bread.)
Pour hot mixture over the bread.
Let stand so the mixture will soak the bread well.
You may sprinkle some cinnamon over it or add some cooked raisins if desired.
Very old recipe.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cook onions in butter until lightly browned.
Add stock and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook 20 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place toast in ovenproof bowl.
Put soup in bowl.
Place Mozzarella cheese on top.
Place under broiler for a few seconds until cheese is lightly browned.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, 3 tablespoons sugar and margarine. Press in pie pan; refrigerate 2 hours.
Mix the cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and Cool Whip; spread into pie shell.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: sauerkraut relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl; mix until blended.
Store in a lightly covered quart jar in refrigerator for 24 hours before serving.

title: refrigerator potato rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Cream shortening and sugar together.
Stir in eggs, mashed potatoes and salt.
Add the dissolved yeast and 1 cup of lukewarm water, drained from the potatoes.
Mix in the flour by hand until dough is easy to handle. Knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl. Cover with damp cloth.
Place in refrigerator.
About two hours before baking time, shape into rolls and let rise in warm place. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix oleo and flour together as for a pie.
Add nuts.
Press mixture on bottom of pie pans.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Cool.
Whip together cream cheese, sugar and 1 cup whipping cream. Spread on cooled baked pie crusts.
Add remaining whipping cream to pudding and milk; spread over cheese mixture.
Refrigerate for several hours, then serve.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Using a strainer, rinse and drain 1 cup of rice with water. In large skillet, brown vermicelli noodles.
Add rinsed rice and heat for a minute, then add the 2 cups of chicken broth/water mixture.
Bring to boil, then cover and simmer until rice is done (approximately 10 to 15 minutes).

title: creamy peach salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Chill until slightly thickened. Blend yogurt into whipped topping, then blend in gelatin.
Stir in peaches and nuts. Pour into 8 x 4 inch loaf pan.
Chill until firm.
About 3 hours.
Garnish with additional peach slices if desired.

title: quick chili
directions: Brown onion in skillet, with a small amount of butter, and hamburger.
Cook until brown; drain.
While hamburger is cooking, open all the canned ingredients and mix in a large pot.
Stir in seasoning mix.
Add cooked hamburger.

title: munchy oyster crackers
directions: Put crackers in brown paper bag.
Mix all other ingredients well and pour over crackers. Shake bag well.
(I then put them in another paper bag to absorb more oil.) Store in Tupperware container.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown floured steak cubes and onion in oil.
Add mushrooms. Add chicken soup and water and cook 30 to 45 minutes on low heat. Add sour cream last and serve over hot rice.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Blend the water, salsa and Village Saucerie.
Cut chicken into strips.
Add to mixture.
Top with the peppers and onions and 1 more tablespoon of Village Saucerie.
Cover dish with foil.
Bake at 400° for 30minutes.
Uncover and bake 5 minutes until chicken is lightly browned.
Serve with tortillas and sour cream.

title: pumpkin spice cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, pumpkin and oil.
Blend in nuts.
Grease and flour two (9-inch) cake pans.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: three fruit pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine three fruits.
Add sugar and tapioca.
Toss to coat.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Let stand 15 minutes, stirring once.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle dash of nutmeg over filling.
Cover with lattice crust.
Cover rim of pie shell with foil.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Remove foil from pie shell and bake 25 minutes longer.
Cool before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery.
Combine all.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 425°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla, blending well.
Combine baking soda and milk; add and mix well.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips, add more if desired.
Bake at 350° for 11 to 13 minutes.

title: broccoli cheddar rolls
directions: Roll dough out into a 12-inch square on lightly floured surface.
Combine broccoli and next 4 ingredients.
Stir.
Spread mixture evenly over dough; leave 1/2-inch border.
Roll dough tightly, jelly roll fashion.
Moisten seam edge with water.
Press securely to seal.
Turn seam side down.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Sprinkle rice evenly
over
9-inch
baking dish. Pour butter evenly over	rice.
Pour mushroom and celery soups and milk over rice and
butter.
Lay
chicken in rows over the rice and soups.
Sprinkle
dry
onion soup over chicken.
Seal pan with foil and bake 1
1/2 hours at 350°.
Do not open oven and peek at all!

title: walnut delight cookies
directions: Mix butter and powdered sugar.
Add remaining ingredients. Roll into balls about 3/4-inch round.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
When cooling, roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: banana punch
directions: Add all ingredients and mix well.
Chill in freezer until slushy.

title: pumpkin-raisin-nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour three 8 1/4 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Combine oil, eggs, water and pumpkin. Sift together into bowl the flour, salt, nutmeg, baking soda, cinnamon and sugar.
Make a well in the center. Add pumpkin mixture and blend until dry ingredients are moistened. Stir in raisins and pecans.
Turn into pans and bake 1 hour.

title: apple cinnamon muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and salt in large bowl.
Beat eggs with milk.
Stir in apple and butter.
Add all at once to flour mixture; stir just until moist. Batter will be very stiff.
Spray muffin pan with vegetable spray and fill 2/3 full.
Combine nuts, brown sugar and remaining 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Sprinkle over each muffin.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: corned beef spread
directions: Boil water and dissolve jello in it.
Mix corned beef, pepper and mayonnaise together.
Add lemon jello mixture and stir. Refrigerate and serve on crackers.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together the sour cream, mayonnaise, eggs and soup.
Stir into defrosted broccoli.
Place layer of Pepperidge Farm herb stuffing in bottom of greased casserole dish.
Place half of broccoli mixture over stuffing.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup Mozzarella cheese and 3/4 cup Cheddar cheese over broccoli.
Add remainder of broccoli.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle good amount of stuffing mix on top.
Drizzle melted margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: graham cracker pie
directions: Blend together and press into 9-inch pie plate.
Save enough crumbs to put on top of pie.
Bake until top edge is brown.

title: meat sauce for spaghetti
directions: Soak mushrooms in water for about 15 minutes; drain and chop. Heat olive oil in heavy saucepan and saute garlic and onion until golden.
Toss the beef with flour; add to onion.
Add wine.
Cook over high heat a few minutes.
Mix in mushrooms, tomatoes, tomato paste, bouillon, salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Cook over low heat 1 1/2 hours.
During the last 1/2 hour of cooking, add basil and Italian seasoning.

title: ricotta balls
directions: In a large bowl mix Ricotta with eggs.
Add all spices, cheese and bread crumbs.
May require more bread crumbs, added gradually until consistency is smooth to handle.
Mix well.
Roll into small football shape.
Carefully fry in hot oil until golden brown on each side.
Drain on paper towel.

title: imitation ham loaf
directions: Mix brown sugar, mustard and vinegar; set aside 1/2 of this for last.
Mix the remaining ingredients with meat mixture and shape into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Baste with sugar mixture or pour over top before baking.
Cut slit in loaf to pour mixture or to baste.

title: grocery bag caramel corn in microwave
directions: Combine brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt.
Cook on Full power for 2 minutes.
Stir well.
Cook 2 more minutes on Full power.
Add soda and stir.
Cut a brown grocery bag to about 8-inches high.
Spray with Pam.
Put popped corn in bag.
Add peanuts if desired.
Pour syrup over the popcorn.
(Make sure syrup is hot.)
Cook on Full power 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir with long handled spoon.
Cook another 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir and cook on Full power 45 seconds.
Pour on wax paper.
Cool.
Store in airtight containers.

title: jello dessert
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix the Cool Whip, sour cream and dry jello.
Cut cherries and nuts; mix together.
Chill approximately 15 minutes and dessert is ready to serve.

title: egg drop soup(microwave)
directions: Pour broth into a 3-quart glass casserole.
Add ginger root slice.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook in microwave oven 12 to 14 minutes at High or until boiling.
Remove ginger root from broth. Stir in sherry and soy sauce.
Blend 3 tablespoons water with the cornstarch until smooth; stir into broth.
Cook uncovered in microwave oven 3 minutes at High; stir once.
Beat eggs and 2 teaspoons water and pour into broth slowly, stirring constantly to form shreds.
Garnish with parsley.

title: sour cherry pineapple salad
directions: Drain juice from cherries; add lemon and orange juice, sugar and jello; bring to boil.
Add gelatin which has been dissolved in 1/4 cup cold water; stir until thoroughly dissolved and mixed; cool.
Add cherries, undrained pineapple, grated rinds, food coloring and nuts.
Turn into large or individual molds and chill until firm.
Yields 12 to 14 servings.

title: chicken barbecue sauce
directions: Beat one egg and add to one cup of vegetable oil.
Thoroughly mix these two ingredients.
Add vinegar, salt, poultry seasoning and pepper.
Mix all these ingredients together.
Thoroughly baste broiler halves every five minutes, until chicken is tender (about 1 hour).
This amount of sauce is good for 10 broiler halves.

title: forty niners
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend well. Pour into greased and floured 12 X 9 inch pan. Bake at 325 degrees for 30 to 35 minutes. Remove from oven and cool thoroughly before slicing into square cookie bars.

title: equal fudgy brownies
directions: Heat margarine, chocolate, milk and apricot preserves in small saucepan, whisking frequently, until chocolate is almost melted.
Remove from heat; whisk until chocolate is melted.
Whisk in egg yolk and vanilla; mix in combined flour, Equal, baking powder and salt until smooth.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar to stiff peaks in large bowl.
Fold chocolate mixture into egg whites; fold in walnuts, if desired.
Pour batter into greased 8-inch square baking pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven until brownies are firm to touch and toothpick comes out clean, 18 to 20 minutes (do not overbake).
Cool on wire rack.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: ham fried rice
directions: Scramble eggs.
Add ham and sprouts.
Then add rice.
Add soy sauce to taste.
Heat to warm.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend peanut butter, shortening, brown sugar, milk and vanilla.
Add eggs and mix.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Mix only until blended.

title: broccoli with pasta
directions: Stir-fry broccoli, garlic and spices in olive oil until broccoli is done to your liking.
While stir-frying, cook and drain pasta.
When broccoli and pasta are done, mix both together (include spices and olive oil) and add Parmesan cheese to your liking.

title: quick fix crab cakes
directions: Mix as directed on back of package of Old Bay crab classic seasoning mix.
Form into medium-size patties.

title: frosting for poppy seed cake
directions: Combine and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cool; spread on cake.
Cover this with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: double peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Cut in shortening and peanut butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Blend in syrup and milk.
Shape in roll 2-inches in diameter; chill.
Slice 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick.
Place half the slices on ungreased cookie sheet.
Spread each with 1/2 teaspoon peanut butter.
Cover with remaining slices.
Seal edges with fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until browned.

title: gram's sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, soda, cream of tartar, salt and vanilla.
Roll and cut.
Sprinkle with colored sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: greek shrimp with rigatoni(another stolen recipe)
directions: Heat oil in skillet and add garlic.
Cook briefly, stirring, and add tomatoes.
Cook about 1 minute and add the wine and salt and pepper.
Add basil and oregano.
Cook over moderate heat for about 10 minutes.

title: creamed onions
directions: Cook onions in boiling water 10 to 15 minutes or until tender. Drain.
Reserve 1/2 cup liquid.
Place onions in hot serving dish.
Melt butter or margarine.
Add flour and seasonings.
Stir until smooth.
Add milk and reserved onion liquid gradually.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour sauce over onions. Sprinkle with paprika.
Serves 6.

title: brandied fruit sauce
directions: To Ferment Fruit:
Combine ingredients.
Place in a glass jar with loose cover.
Stir several times the first day, then stir once a day.
At end of 2 weeks, starter has fermented enough to make sauce.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bring to a boil and simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Good with beef or pork.
Also good on grilled chicken.

title: mushroom-onion pie
directions: Heat butter.
Add onions and saute until transparent.
Wipe mushrooms with damp cloth.
Add to onions and cook, stirring occasionally, 4 to 5 minutes.
Stir in flour.

title: shrimp or crawfish etouffee
directions: Saute onions, celery, tomatoes and seasoning for about 30 minutes.
Add juice of lemon, dash of Worcestershire sauce, parsley and garlic.
Cover pot.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Add shrimp or crawfish about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Saute onion in butter; add chopped broccoli.
Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Grind raw cranberries, orange rind, pineapple and sugar.
Then add to already made jello mix.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: crock-pot beef tips
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook 5 to 6 hours on low. Serve over rice or corn muffins.

title: russian tea
directions: Boil for a few minutes; set aside.
When cool, put in refrigerator.
Heat when needed.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add egg, milk and oil.
Beat until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Drop by tablespoons into hot skillet with small amount of oil.
Cook until golden brown.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Stir and heat all ingredients. Place in baking dish. Place biscuits on top. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes, until biscuits are done.

title: mexican pralines
directions: Combine brown sugar, milk and syrup.
Cook over medium heat until mixture forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat and add butter, vanilla and pecans.
Beat and drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Let cool completely.

title: brownie pie
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate squares in pie pan.
Add sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Add eggs, vanilla and nuts.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: golden crumb broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli; drain well.
Arrange drained broccoli in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, cheese, pimiento and lemon juice.
Pour over broccoli.
Top with crushed crackers. Bake at 350°, uncovered for 35 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: quick monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon and pecans.
Cut biscuits into fourths. Layer in tube pan 1 layer biscuits, 1 layer sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Melt brown sugar and butter until blended.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.
Best served warm.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown chops
in
skillet.
Place
on
rice in bottom of fairly large
casserole.	Pour
chops'
drippings
over this. Place a thick
slice
of
onion,
tomato and ring of pepper on each chop. Salt and pepper as you go.	Pour consomme over all and sprinkle with several pinches of marjoram and thyme.

title: shrimp au gratin
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons butter in saucepan.
Saute onion.
Stir in flour, salt, mustard and pepper.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture is bubbly.
Add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until sauce thickens and bubbles.
Add 3/4 cup cheese; stir until melted.
Add shrimp and mushrooms to sauce.
Turn into a buttered 6-cup shallow baking dish.
Combine crumbs and remaining cheese.
Sprinkle over top of dish.
Dot with remaining 1 tablespoon butter.
Bake in hot oven, 400°, for 10 minutes or until sauce is bubbly and top is lightly browned.
Makes 4 servings.
May also be baked in individual ramekins.

title: pineapple-cheese casserole
directions: Mix pineapple juice and flour, mixing well.
Add sugar and mix.
Add pineapple tidbits and grated cheese.
Pour into baking dish.
Mix crushed Ritz crackers with melted margarine and pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: italian meatballs
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine bread crumbs, pepper, salt, garlic powder, milk and egg.
Mix thoroughly. Add ground chuck and mix again. Roll into firm, well shaped small balls.
Brown meatballs and finish cooking in sauce prior to serving.

title: marinated mushroom -spinach salad
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
Add mushrooms and let stand at room temperature 2 hours or refrigerate overnight, stirring occasionally.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Beat in a bowl the eggs. Combine in a separate bowl the onions, soup and mayonnaise. Add

beaten eggs. Mix thoroughly. Place mixture in a casserole dish. Add cooked and drained cauliflower. Melt butter. Add bread crumbs. Mix well. Sprinkle over cauliflower mixture. Place in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: rachel pafford's wassail
directions: Combine cider and sugar in a large saucepan.
Tie allspice, cloves and cinnamon sticks in cheesecloth and add to cider.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Remove spices and add other juices and water.
Heat and serve.
Garnish with orange and lemon slices, if desired.

title: garlicky carrots
directions: Melt butter in frying pan.
Add crushed garlic and stir for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add carrots, stirring until hot.
Add salt to taste.

title: groovie chewie
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and press into a 9 x 12-inch cake pan.

title: crab bisque(serves 6)
directions: Put crab meat in a bowl, pour sherry over and let stand 1 hour.
Blend together tomato and green pea soups, cream, curry and paprika.
Heat slowly, but do not boil.
Add crab meat.
Reheat to boiling point (do not boil) and serve immediately.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Saute pepper, onion and celery.
Add rice, soup, water and sausage.
Place in covered baking dish and bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cherry berries on a cloud
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
Cover baking sheet with heavy brown paper. Draw outline of heart, 9 inches across greatest width, on paper. Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until foamy.
Beat in 3/4 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time; continue beating until stiff and glossy.
Do not underbeat!
Spoon meringue into outline on paper, building up side.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn off oven; leave meringue in oven with door closed for 1 hour.
Remove from oven; finish cooling away from draft.

title: mom's date loaf delight
directions: Chop dates.
Add water (boiling) and soda.
Set aside to cool, stirring occasionally.
Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add nuts and mix.
Sift salt, flour and spices; stir into creamed mixture, alternately with date mixture.
Line bottom of greased pan with waxed paper.
Bake in hot oven 400° to 425° for 20 minutes, then 1 hour at 250° or until tests done with a toothpick. Keeps well!

title: fat-free butterscotch crisps
directions: Combine the margarine or butter, sugar, egg substitute, molasses and vanilla extract in the bowl of a food processor or electric mixer and process until smooth.
In a separate bowl, combine the flour and baking soda. Add the flour mixture to the margarine mixture and process to mix well. Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Coat a baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray. Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of dough onto the baking sheet, placing them 1 1/2-inches apart.
Bake at 300° for about 16 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool the cookies on the pan for 1 minute. Transfer the cookies to wire racks and cool completely. Serve immediately or transfer to an airtight container.

title: lilly may's pecan pie
directions: Combine syrup, honey, sugar and butter; bring to a boil gently for 5 minutes.
Stir in pecans.
Combine eggs, dash of salt and vanilla.
Pour syrup into eggs; beat well.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked crust.
Bake for 30 minutes, or until done, at 375°.

title: oven fried chicken in barbecue sauce
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Dip chicken into sauce; place in bowl.
Pour remaining sauce over chicken and marinate for 2 hours. Roll chicken in crumbs.
Place in large baking pan; let stand for 30 minutes.
Spoon butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mock wild rice
directions: Melt oleo at low heat.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cover. Simmer for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: bayou bracer
directions: In
a blender, combine lime juice and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Add
1 quart of sparkling water and juice of 1 lime. Put
all
ingredients
from blender into punch bowl and add the other bottle of sparkling water.
Just before serving, add
the lime and pineapple sherbet.
Garnish with lime slices and mint leaves.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: pineapple smoothie
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup juice.
Freeze pineapple chunks.
Place juice, buttermilk, vanilla, sweetener and frozen pineapple into a blender container.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into glasses and garnish with mint, if desired.
Serve immediately.
Yield:
5 servings (74 calories).

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Take one cup of broth and set aside to cool.
Put the rest of the broth back in pot.

title: chocolate velvet pie
directions: In a double boiler over hot, not boiling water, melt chocolate morsels.
Stir until smooth.
In a large bowl, mix cream cheese, melted chocolate and vanilla extract.
Beat until fluffy and light.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm.
Garnish with whipped cream.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown beef in a little oil until very brown.
Add the beef stew mix, salt and pepper and cook a little longer.
(May stick to bottom of put but that's okay.)
Add carrots, celery and onions. Add water but pot should be no more than 3/4's full.
Cook for about 1 hour until meat is tender.
After cooker has cooled, add the potatoes.
Cook until done.
Using 1/2 cup flour, salt, pepper and enough milk to make a smooth paste, add to the stew and mix well.
More milk may be used to make more gravy.

title: brown bread
directions: Combine bran, milk, raisins, molasses and sugar. Sift flour with salt and soda.
Add to the first mixture, stirring until flour disappears.
Pour batter into greased can (large). Cover tightly with aluminum and steam for 3 hours.

title: apple chess pie
directions: Cream sugar and oleo together.
Add flour and eggs; mix well. Add apples or peaches and cinnamon.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake for 10 minutes at 400°; reduce heat to 325° and bake an additional 40 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed.
Rinse in cold water and drain well. Put in serving bowl and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: sweet potato fluff
directions: Combine all ingredients and spoon into a casserole dish. Grease dish with margarine.

title: pork hock dinner
directions: Wash hocks and place in large pot.
Cover with hot water, add 2 teaspoons salt (if fresh meat) and simmer covered until meat is nearly tender (about 1 1/2 hours).
Add carrots, chopped peeled onions and pared potatoes, cut in half.
Cover and cook for 15 minutes.
Add cabbage, cut in wedges and cook covered for 15 minutes longer or until vegetables are tender.
Sprinkle vegetables with salt, pepper and paprika.
Serves 4.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookie dough into 1/8-inch slices; place on greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Press together.
Bake 15 minutes in a 350° oven, then cool.

title: hamburger-vegetable casserole
directions: Break up hamburger and place in a 1 quart casserole.
Add a layer of each of the vegetables, sliced fine.
Sprinkle some salt between each layer.
Mix mushroom soup with water and pour over mixture.
In a 300° oven, bake for 1 1/4 hours, covered, and 1/2 hour uncovered.
Serves 4.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a prepared Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: pork chops
directions: Brown the pork chops on both sides in frying pan. Place in casserole dish after browning. Put the soup on top of pork chops and cover with tinfoil. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: toffee banana cream pie
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Prepare pie crust according to package directions for unfilled one crust pie, using a 9-inch pie pan. (Refrigerate remaining crust.)
Bake for 9 to 11 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool completely.
In small bowl, combine cream cheese and caramel topping; beat until smooth.
Spread over bottom of cooled crust.
Arrange banana slices over cream cheese mixture. Reserve 2 tablespoons toffee bars; sprinkle remaining candy bars over banana slices.
Beat whipping cream, brown sugar and vanilla until stiff peaks form.
Spread over pie.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
Just before serving, garnish with rest of toffee bars and banana slices.
Keep refrigerated!

title: banana pudding
directions: In a
large mixing bowl, blend pudding mix in milk with wire whisk.
Add
sour
cream
and 1/2 whipped topping, mixing well. Set aside.

title: evelyn coconut cake
directions: Fix cake mix as directed; pour in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake as directed on box.
Bring to boil the sugar and milk in saucepan on top of stove.
After cake is cooked, immediately pierce holes in cake with fork.
Pour milk and sugar mixture on cake; cool.
Mix Cool Whip, nuts and coconut together.
Spread on cool cake.

title: oven style caramel corn
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in a 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil; boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Do not overboil.
Add vanilla and soda, stirring after each addition.
Pour over salted popped corn, covering all kernels.
Place on 2 cookie sheets. Bake in a 250° oven for 1 hour, stirring 3 to 4 times.
(May be stored in any tight can or plastic bag.)
Cool on wax paper.
I put peanuts and pecans in mine.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Drain all but 1 can beans; set aside.
In large saucepot, saute carrots, green pepper, onion and garlic in oil 5 minutes. Stir in reserved beans, tomatoes, molasses, chili powder, ground cumin, dried oregano and bay leaf.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Uncover; simmer 15 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Salt to taste.
Serve over bed of brown rice.

title: broccoli-ravioli casserole
directions: Cut broccoli spears into serving size pieces; place on bottom of casserole dish.
Mix ravioli and sour cream; pour over broccoli.
Top with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 to 45 minutes or until cheese is golden brown.
Makes approximately 6 servings.

title: perfect peppermint patties
directions: In a bowl, combine first 4 ingredients.
Add milk and mix well.
Roll into 1-inch balls and place on a waxed paper-lined cookie sheet.
Chill for 20 minutes.
Flatten with a glass to 1/4 inch; chill for 30 minutes.
In a double boiler or microwave-safe bowl, melt chocolate chips and shortening.
Dip patties; place on waxed paper to harden.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: tuna balls
directions: Mix the first five ingredients well; place in refrigerator until cold.
Shape into balls and roll in parsley flakes.

title: molasses gingerbread
directions: Sift together the white flour, salt and ginger.
Add soda to the molasses.
Combine mixtures.
Add butter and milk; beat vigorously.
Pour into greased pan and bake in a moderate oven for about 35 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Grease large casserole dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 of stuffing mix on bottom.
Combine first 5 ingredients and mix well.
Pour over stuffing mix in casserole.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing mix over squash.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 20 to 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: rice and black beans
directions: Hint:
Chop all veggies.
Open cans and have herbs and seasonings close by.
Cooking is easy and fast.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans and mix ingredients together.
Cover and refrigerate for 6 hours or overnight.

title: marble squares
directions: Combine cream cheese, 1/3 cup sugar, 1 egg and mix well in medium bowl.
Set aside.
Boil in small pan oleo, water and chocolate squares; remove from heat.
Mix 2 cups flour and 2 cups sugar together in large bowl.
Stir in hot chocolate mixture.
Add 2 eggs, sour cream, soda and salt; mix well.
Grease and flour a 15.5 x 10.5-inch jelly roll pan; pour chocolate batter in pan. Spread cream cheese with a spoon over top of chocolate batter and knife in marble effect.
Sprinkle chocolate chips all over top and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: butter nut pound cake
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients.
Add eggs, beating well.
Add milk and flour, alternately, ending with flour.
Fold in flavoring by hand.
Pour into greased tube pan and place in a cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Do not open door while baking. Remove from pan immediately.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired, when cool.

title: potato casserole
directions: Defrost potatoes until you can break apart.
Combine all ingredients, except for the corn flakes and 1/4 cup of butter. Pour ingredients into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Top with 1 cup crushed corn flakes and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Saute meat, onion and green pepper; drain.
Combine with spaghetti sauce, honey and oregano; set aside.

title: mexican rice
directions: Cook all ingredients and mix all together.
Simmer on medium heat for 10 minutes.
Keep moist with water, if needed.

title: canadian style pea soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in pan and simmer for 2 hours.
Remove bay leaves before serving.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together in saucepan.
Add milk and butter.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, boiling one minute. Remove from heat, stirring in oats and peanut butter.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: buttermilk lemon pie
directions: Add soda to buttermilk.
Add salt and flour to sugar and half of buttermilk-soda mixture for a thick paste.
Put in egg yolks and add remainder of milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add butter, grated rind and juice of lemon.
When cool, pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: corn pudding
directions: If fresh corn, cook in as little amount of water as possible. Beat eggs in milk.
Add rest of ingredients and bake in moderate oven at 350° until knife blade comes out clean (usually 50 to 60 minutes).

title: potato chowder
directions: Cook potatoes, celery, onion, green pepper, carrots, parsley, butter, salt and pepper in a small amount of water; simmer until tender.
Add soups and milk; simmer 5 to 10 minutes longer.

title: 7 layer dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise and sour cream before spreading.
Layer ingredients as listed above...chill.
Serve with Tortilla Chips!

title: cheese apples
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt, cut in butter until coarse; mix in cheese and set aside.
Mix water and lemon juice.
Pour over apples and toss.
Place in 8-inch square pan.
Spread topping over apples and pat down.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: delta point cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add sugar and beat well. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and lemon juice.
Pour into crumb crust in spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour.
Then add topping and bake 15 more minutes.

title: never fail noodles
directions: Stir eggs, salt, baking powder and butter together.
Working in flour, make soft dough.
Roll, flour and cut.
Cook with beef or chicken broth.

title: to freeze rhubarb
directions: Bring sugar and rhubarb to a boil.
Add jello and Sure-Jell. Stir well.
Remove from heat.
Pour into sterilized jars. Cover and freeze.

title: apple snicker salad
directions: Combine all ingredients into a large mixing bowl.
Chill and serve.

title: savory cheese muffins(makes soup or salads special)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease muffin pans.
Combine flour, cheese, mustard and chili powder in mixing bowl; set aside.
In another bowl, beat egg; stir in milk and oil.
Add liquid ingredients all at once to flour mixture.
Stir only until flour is moistened.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake about 18 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 12 muffins.

title: crock-pot potato soup
directions: Put all ingredients, except evaporated milk in crock-pot. Cover and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours (high: 3 to 4 hours). Stir in milk during the last hour.
If desired, mash potatoes before serving.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease a Bundt or angel food cake pan.
Cut each biscuit into quarters and roll into balls.
In a bowl, combine sugar and cinnamon.
Roll each biscuit piece in the sugar mixture.
Pile into the buttered cake pan.

title: date pudding
directions: Put soda in water and pour over dates; let cool.
Add sugar, butter, flour and egg.
Blend in nuts.
Bake at 350° until shiny on top and done with toothpick touch.
Cool and serve with whipped cream.

title: molded avocado salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add salt, lemon juice, horseradish and grated onion.
Cool.
Fold in avocados and celery. Pour in 1 1/2-quart ring mold.
Serve with Herb Mayonnaise. Serves 6 to 8.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a fluted pan (bundt pan, or loaf pan).
Mix sugar and cinnamon together in a small bowl.
Cut each biscuit into quarters and coat each with cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Arrange in pan (fill about 3/4 of the pan).

title: grandma bee's red clam sauce
directions: All tomatoes, celery, onion, garlic and parsley to be chopped fine.
Saute garlic, onion and celery; do not brown. Saute until tender.
Add the plum tomatoes, tomato paste, wine, clam juice, oregano, basil, pepper flakes (takes more for really hot) and sun-dried tomatoes (did you remember to soften first and dice fine).
Simmer all ingredients 35 to 45 minutes.
Add clams and parsley.
Simmer 10 minutes. Serve immediately over fresh pasta with French bread.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pumpkin log
directions: Unroll cake; remove paper.
Spread cream cheese mixture over cake.
Re-roll; chill.
Refrigerate.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix ground beef, bell pepper, onion and salt.
Cook in a heavy skillet until done.
Combine lettuce, tomatoes, kidney beans, cheese, hot sauce and Catalina dressing.
Mix all ingredients and serve.

title: classic quiche lorraine
directions: Bake pie crust at 450° for 10 minutes.
In a skillet, cook bacon until crisp; drain, reserving 2 tablespoons of the drippings.
Finely crumble bacon and set aside.
Cook onion in the reserved drippings until tender; drain.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Melt butter; add flour and stir.
Gradually add soup and milk. Add onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook over low heat until smooth and thick, stirring constantly.
Cook cabbage in small amount of water and salt.
Boil 8 minutes.
Drain and add sauce. Mix.
Place in baking dish.
Top with shredded cheese.
Place in oven until cheese is melted.

title: scottish oat cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat the butter with the sugars until light and fluffy.
Add the egg and syrup and mix.
Sift in the flour and baking powder and add the oats.
Stir until well mixed together. Put heaped teaspoonfuls of the mixture onto a greased cookie sheet and flatten slightly.
Bake for 12 minutes, then lift onto a cake rack.
The cookies will be slightly soft, but they'll become firm and chewy when they cool down.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Crush graham crackers and mix 1 stick of melted margarine. Place in 8 x 9-inch cake pan.
Stand 1/2 of graham crackers along side of pan. Bake at 350°. Let cool.

title: black beans and rice
directions: Heat black beans.
Cook rice.
Place 1/2 can beans on top of hot cooked rice.
Heat chopped onions and cover with salsa.
Serve with a large green salad using nonfat dressing.
Serves 2.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, water and eggs as directed. Bake cake in two 9-inch layer pans, well oiled and lined with waxed paper. Cool completely. Slice each layer with a thread to make 4 layers.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Slice potatoes.
Cook until done.
Beat all ingredients together.
Put in deep-dish pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pretzel dip
directions: Beat all ingredients with mixer until smooth.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef and onion, stir in flour.
Add salt, pepper and mushrooms; cook 5 minutes.
Add can of soup and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Add more salt, if desired.
Serve over rice.

title: deer camp chili
directions: Brown venison and 1/2 onion.
Combine tomatoes, chili mix, bell pepper, onion, mushrooms and beans in big pot.
Add meat and let simmer for 1 hour.

title: bean relish to can
directions: Grind onions and peppers.
Cook beans, carrots and celery until tender (not soft).

title: quick ambrosia
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; stir.
Let set 2 hours.
Add Cool Whip and serve.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Yields 4 servings.

title: fruit cream pie
directions: Baking Temperature: 375°.
Baking Time: 35 to 40 minutes.

title: german fudge
directions: Boil the sugar, salt, butter and milk for 6 minutes.
In a bowl, put the remaining ingredients.
Pour hot mixture over this and beat until chocolate is melted and well mixed.
Pour into pan, greased with butter.
Let set several hours before cutting.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Spray a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Preheat oven to 350°. Combine cake mix, water and egg. Mix according to package directions.
Pour into pan and bake for 15 to 18 minutes. (Cake layer will be thin.) Cool cake in pan.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Mix soups and rice.
Add water and set aside.
Place chicken in greased casserole dish and pour soup mixture over chicken.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Please don't peek.

title: double batch ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine shortening, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Beat eggs into creamed mixture.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix into creamed mixture just until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecan pieces.

title: coconut pyramids
directions: Using egg cups, pack mixture into cup.
After packing, run egg cup under cold water to allow mixture to come out.
Must do each time.
Place pyramids on wax paper on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for approximately 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes in 3/4-inch slices. Drain slightly on paper towel. Season with pinch of salt. Place 3 shallow dishes on work place. Spread flour in 1 dish. Beat eggs in 2nd dish; in 3rd dish, mix cornmeal, Parmesan, red pepper, salt and pepper. Coat tomato slices with flour. Dip in egg. Coat with cornmeal mixture. Heat 3 tablespoons oil in large skillet over medium-high heat. Add tomato slices. Cook 3 to 4 minutes on each side until golden and crispy. Add more oil as needed. Serve warm.

title: mile high strawberry pie
directions: Put defrosted strawberries, sugar, egg whites, salt and lemon juice in large bowl.
Beat until stiff (15 minutes).
Whip the cream.
Add vanilla and fold into strawberry mixture.
Pile into pie shell.
Freeze overnight.
Can be made with other frozen fruits.

title: broccoli-lima bean casserole
directions: Cook frozen vegetables as per directions.
Drain. Put half in bottom of buttered 2-quart casserole.
Put half of the water chestnuts on top.
Mix sour cream, onion soup mix and mushroom soup.
Put half of this mixture on vegetables.
Repeat.
Top with Rice Krispies and dot with butter.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Serves 6.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli according to package and drain.
Mix soup, cheese, mayo and onions.
Blend in eggs.
Toss lightly with drained broccoli.
Put into a greased casserole dish.
Mix bread crumbs with melted butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake uncovered for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter until tender and lightly brown. Sprinkle flour over onions an cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add water and instant beef bouillon; heat to boiling.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: hamburger baked beans
directions: Cook and drain well the hamburger meat. Chop onion and bell pepper. In a large pot, add all ingredients. Simmer over low heat for 1 hour. Stir often to keep from sticking. (May bake in the oven, if desired.)

title: parmesan zucchini
directions: Heat oil in covered frying pan to medium heat.
Add garlic (chopped) and saute.
Add bell pepper, celery and onion.
Saute until onion is tender.
Add squash, tomatoes and seasoning to mixture.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and let simmer on medium heat until vegetables are tender and mixture has thickened. Serve in dish with Parmesan cheese covering top.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Mix cabbage and white sauce together.
Put a layer of cabbage in a greased baking dish.
Add a layer of crumbs and repeat process until all ingredients are used.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake in a hot oven for about 20 minutes or until brown at 375°.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar and chocolate in boiler.
Add milk and Karo (stir). Place over medium heat and cook, stirring until candy forms a ball in glass of water.
Add butter and flavoring; stir until nearly thick.
Add pecans and stir until thick.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Reserve broth from chicken and use to mix Stove Top.
Leave out butter on box.
Mix in order.
Saute onions and celery in stick of butter.
Add sour cream and mushroom soup.
Bake in medium dish at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all the ingredients together; drop by teaspoonful into hot grease.
Fry until golden brown.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Stir in molasses. Sift dry ingredients together and add.
Shape into balls and roll in about 1/2 cup sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Can double the recipe.

title: fig jam
directions: Mix together and let stand 30 minutes.
Then boil 5 minutes. Pour in hot jars and seal.
Makes about 3 pints.

title: brownie cakes
directions: In a bowl, beat flour, sugar, eggs, and yolk until smooth. In a saucepan, melt butter, chocolate, and salt over medium heat. Remove from heat; add to flour mixture, and stir.
Refrigerate three hours.
Bake in greased cupcake pan for 20 minutes at 375°F. Let cool.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown and drain meat; add taco seasonings as stated on package.
Add cans of Veg-All (drained), soups, water, Ro-Tel and Velveeta.
Mix well.
Simmer in large pot on stove until hot. Crumble a handful of chips in bowl and pour soup on top.

title: tangy mustard cauliflower
directions: Place cauliflower and water in 1 1/2-quart glass casserole. Cover with glass lid.
Microwave for 9 minutes on High.
Drain. Combine mayonnaise, onion, mustard and salt in small mixing bowl. Spoon mustard sauce on top of cauliflower.
Sprinkle with cheese. Microwave for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes on Roast to heat topping and melt cheese.
Let stand 2 minutes before serving.

title: mermaid pie
directions: Melt margarine; mix with flour and pecans and pat in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: honey-almond chicken(weight watchers)
directions: Sprinkle chicken with flour; dip in egg and coat with bread crumbs.
In 12-inch nonstick skillet, heat 2 tablespoons oil.
Add chicken and cook 3 to 4 minutes on each side.
Remove to platter and keep warm.
In same pan, saute almonds until lightly toasted (1 to 2 minutes).

title: mexican fudge
directions: Grate all cheeses; mix in eggs (scrambled) and jalapeno peppers.
Bake in large Pyrex dish (sprayed with Pam) at 300° for approximately 40 to 45 minutes or until cheese begins to brown. Let cool about an hour before serving.

title: lemon bars
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients like pie crust.
Pat into a 10 x 15-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Beat eggs; add sugar and rest of ingredients.
Pour over crust when it is baked and return to the oven for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix last 4 ingredients together.
Heat to boiling and remove from the heat.
Cool.
Pour over sliced cucumbers, onions and peppers that have been mixed together in a large jar.
Keep in the refrigerator until used.
Will keep up to a year!!!!

title: white fudge
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients for 10 minutes; stir constantly. Remove from heat.
Add butter and stir until dissolved.
Add vanilla chips.
Add vanilla flavoring.
Add walnuts.
Pour into lightly greased 7 x 9-inch pan.
Cool in refrigerator at least 1 hour.
Cut into squares.

title: creamy top fruit salad
directions: Combine cream cheese, juice and peel, mixing until well blended.
Beat whipping cream until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold into cream cheese mixture; chill.
Layer fruit in 2 1/2 quart glass serving bowl. Top with cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired. Chill.
Serves 8.

title: ice cream cookies
directions: Soften butter and cream together with softened ice cream. Blend in flour. Chill dough overnight or for several hours. Flour hands and break off bits of dough the size of a walnut. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with thumb.
Put a dab of filling in center. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: bow ties(polish kruszciki)
directions: Roll 1/3 at a time real thin.
Cut 1 1/2 x 2-inch strips. Make hole in middle.
Pull one end through hole.
Fry in deep Crisco 1/2 minute on each side and drain.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Combine potatoes and onion.
Squeeze out all excess liquid. Mix all ingredients together except butter and oil.
Let sit 5 minutes.

title: shortcake
directions: Cut shortening into flour, salt, baking powder and sugar. Fold in beaten egg, vanilla and milk until all dry ingredients are moistened and folded in.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
To serve, cut in half and spoon 4 cups crushed strawberries or other seasonal fruit.
Top with whipped cream.

title: turnip slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; stir well.
Cover and chill.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: In a bowl, combine the sweetened condensed milk, lemon juice and rind, egg yolks and food coloring; mix well.
In another bowl, beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff, but not dry. Fold egg whites into milk and lemon mixture.
Pour into crust. Chill 3 hours or until set.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Makes 4 small loaves. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: heath ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients except for chips.
Pour into ice cream freezer.
When almost set, add both chips.

title: colossal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream margarine, brown sugar and sugar. Add vanilla and eggs.
Mix well.
Add baking powder and peanut butter.
Stir in oatmeal and chocolate chips.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: chocolate fruit cake(makes 4 pounds)
directions: Rinse and drain raisins.
Rinse apricots and chop.
Combine raisins, apricots, walnuts and candied fruits.
Dice marshmallows and combine with milk, orange rind and vanilla.
Add cookie crumbs and mix well.
Mix in fruits and walnuts.
Pack into oiled tube pan or gelatin mold.
Cover with waxed paper or aluminum foil. Chill one week or longer before cutting.

title: granny's fudge
directions: Put the sugar and milk in pan; bring to a boil for 7 minutes. Take off fire.
Add the chocolate chips, marshmallows and chopped pecans; mix well.
Pour onto buttered dish.

title: frying batter
directions: Combine flour, baking soda and salt in bowl.
Mix well.
Add beaten eggs and milk.
Mix until batter is smooth.

title: blueberry muffins (lo-cal)
directions: Sift dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Work in margarine with hands until mixed well.
Add milk until all moistened.
Bake at 350° in muffin pan sprayed with nonstick oil.
Bake until lightly browned.

title: orange cream cake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine cake, drink mix, eggs, water and oil. Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into an ungreased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Using meat fork, poke holes in cake.
Cool on wire rack for 30 minutes.

title: cannoli cake
directions: Combine cream cheese, Ricotta cheese, sugar, milk, vanilla and almond.
Mix at medium speed until well blended.
Stir in chocolate pieces.
Split cake lengthwise into 4 layers.
Spread three layers with cream cheese mixture; stack layers.
Top with remaining layer and frost.
Chill and serve.

title: sausage balls
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet.
In large bowl, combine sausage, cheese, milk and egg and blend well.
Lightly spoon pancake mix into measuring cup, level off.
Add pancake mix, pepper and onion soup mix; mix well.
Roll into 1-inch balls; place on prepared cookie sheet; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately and serve warm.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen balls.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Melt margarine and peanut butter.
Add rest of ingredients. Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: rice krispie balls
directions: Cook
margarine,
sugar,
egg,	vanilla and dates for 8 minutes
or
until	thick,	stirring constantly.
Cool and add Rice Krispies,
nuts
and
grated orange rind.
Shape in small balls and roll in chopped nuts, coconut or powdered sugar.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift flour with sugar, soda and salt. Beat eggs in mixing bowl until thick and lemon colored. Add drained fruit. Stir in dry ingredients. Mix thoroughly. Pour into greased and floured dish. Sprinkle brown sugar over top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Serve warm or cold.

title: quick donuts
directions: Poke hole in each biscuit with 2 fingers.
Deep fry until golden brown, then drain and shake in sugar and cinnamon.
Enjoy!

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then press meat mixture into loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cauliflower
directions: Steam cauliflower for 5 or 6 minutes; break it up into flowerets and take out of steamer.
Add soup and milk.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs, cheese and a little paprika.
Brown lightly in a 350° oven.

title: easy hot rolls
directions: Melt yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Pour boiling water over salt, sugar and shortening; let cool.
Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Add flour a little at a time.
(Sometimes I use a little less than 4 cups.)
Let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and roll out into small balls.
Let rise and bake at 400° until brown. Can be refrigerated for a few days before baking.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs and milk.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Add pumpkin.
Mix all together.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 medium sized muffins.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Toss together; leave a little bacon for the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip together. Boil until rolling boil, apricot Jell-O, water and sugar.
Cool real good.
Peel peaches and slice.
Pour cream cheese mixture into pie crust.
Add sliced peaches.
Pour apricot mixture on top of this.

title: tangy carrots
directions: Cook carrots until just tender.
Drain, saving 1/4 cup of cooking liquid.
Place carrots in greased ovenproof serving dish. In small bowl, combine reserved liquid with mayonnaise, onion, horseradish and salt.
Spread over carrots.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs, paprika and parsley.
Bake at 375° uncovered for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach as directed and drain.
Mix in all other items. Shape into balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or freeze and bake later.

title: pasta salad with tuna
directions: Marinate broccoli and carrots in dressing 1 to 2 hours.
Mix together pasta, tuna, vegetables and dressing.
Serve.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese and Old English soften at room temperature. Cream together and add remaining ingredients.
Cream until uniform in color.
Form ball and refrigerate.
Spread on crackers.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Thoroughly mix dry ingredients in medium saucepan. Add milk and cook until thick. Remove from heat. Add butter and vanilla. Refrigerate. May be served reheated or cold. Good on plain cake or for ice cream sundae.

title: english tipsy trifle
directions: In 2-inch deep dish, spread ladyfingers.
Cover with strawberry preserves; pour on Amaretto or sherry and sprinkle on nuts.
Chop peaches and sprinkle on top.
Mix jello according to directions, using 1/2 cup less water, and pour evenly over ingredients in dish. Let set.
Make custard as directed on package; this can be substituted with instant vanilla pudding.
If using custard, let cool before pouring over set jello.
Refrigerate.
Just before serving, add whipped cream as topping.

title: butterscotch pudding or pie filling
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour, eggs and vanilla together.
Now boil milk, when it comes to a boil, add butter and other ingredients. Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Makes 1 pie.

title: thick and creamy eggnog
directions: Beat egg whites (at room temperature) until foamy.
Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar, beating until stiff peaks form; set aside. Prepare whipped topping mix according to package directions; set aside.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Gradually add remaining sugar and bourbon, beating well.
Fold yolk/bourbon mixture and prepared whipped topping into egg whites.
Spoon eggnog into individual serving glasses and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Yields about 2 quarts.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes, ham, onion and cheese in casserole dish.
Heat soup and milk together.
Pour on potato mixture; salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until tender.
This can also be cooked in a slow cooker.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: eclairs
directions: Place a layer of graham crackers in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix instant pudding and milk. Then mix in the Cool Whip. Pour over layer of graham crackers.
Then place another layer of graham crackers.
Let set awhile.
Mix cocoa, melted butter, powdered sugar and hot water.
Pour over graham crackers, covering pudding mixture.
Refrigerate overnight or 6 to 8 hours.

title: doughnuts
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
To this mixture add eggs and milk; beat together.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Roll out dough. Cut with doughnut cutter.
Fry in oil until brown.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix flour with butter and confectioners sugar until it holds together.
Press into 9 x 12-inch baking pan and bake at 350° for about 8 to 10 minutes.
Beat together eggs, granulated sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Fold in 4 to 4 1/2 tablespoons flour and baking powder.
Pour over hot crust and bake 20 to 25 minutes or until set at 350°.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar while warm. Cut while warm.
Use jellyroll pan if thinner squares are desired.

title: chicken tarragon
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Sprinkle over chicken.
Brown slowly in butter.
Remove from pan (use same pan).
Cook onion until tender.
(Move onion aside.)
Add chicken, mushrooms and tarragon.
Spoon onions over chicken.
Add water and cover.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Put in oblong pan and bake at 400° for 15 minutes, stirring 2 or 3 times.
Take out about 1/2 mixture and flatten rest in bottom of pan.

title: chocolate eclair delight
directions: Lay crackers flat in 9 x 13-inch pan. Add milk to instant pudding and beat until thick. Fold in Cool Whip. Layer pudding on top of graham crackers. Cover pudding with another layer of graham crackers.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients; add chopped onions and peppers, then beat milk and egg together and add to mixture.
Drop small spoonfuls into hot grease.

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: Use a 2 cup measure and fill to the brim with flour. Put into sifter. Add baking powder, and salt and set aside. Beat eggs with mixer. Using the same cup as above, fill to 2 cup line with sugar, and add to eggs. Beat this mixture some more. Put milk in a saucepan and add butter and heat to boiling. Add flour mixture to eggs and sugar then add hot milk vanilla and lemon. Mix well.

title: apple dip
directions: Whip softened cream cheese with jam.
Gently fold in topping until evenly blended.
A great fruit dip especially for apples.

title: scalloped french green beans
directions: Cook frozen green beans according to package directions.
If you use canned beans, drain and use straight from can.
Mix beans with soup, put into casserole dish, top with French fried onions and bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: vegetable cole slaw
directions: Grate cabbage in large bowl.
Dice onions, cucumbers and tomatoes; toss into cabbage.
In small bowl mix mayonnaise, sugar, mustard, salt and pepper until well blended.
Add mayonnaise mixture to cabbage.
Mix well.
Toss in grated carrots.
Makes 12 servings.

title: nina's brown sugar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Cook for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain pasta; cool. Add pineapple, pudding and oranges. Mix well. Let set 4 hours or overnight. Add Cool Whip; mix well and serve.

title: oven chicken
directions: Wash and cut up chicken.
Sprinkle with season salt as you would regular salt.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix jello, peanuts and water.
Let chill in fridge for 20 minutes.
Add pineapple, cherries and whipped cream.
Let it set in fridge until ready to eat.

title: spinach pie with muenster crust
directions: Line a 10-inch pie plate with overlapping slices of Muenster cheese, covering the bottom and 3/4 of the way up the sides. Combine spinach, squash, cottage cheese, eggs, onion, Parmesan cheese, dill and pepper. Spread mixture over cheese evenly.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Allow to stand 5 minutes before slicing. Serves 4 to 6 slices.

title: baked turkey and rice casserole
directions: Combine both soups, milk and rice and pour into 3 qt. baking dish. Top with turkey. Sprinkle with onion soup mix. Cover with foil. Bake at 325° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours, or until turkey is tender.

title: sausage-egg bake
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch Pyrex baking dish, place broken bread pieces; add layer of sausage, then layer of grits.
Mix together eggs, milk and cheese, then pour over top.
Let stand overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pizza bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Split Italian bread lengthwise. Spread mix on halves.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.
Put on cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: party chicken
directions: Put dried beef on bottom of 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Wrap chicken breasts with bacon.
Top with equal parts of sour cream and cream of mushroom soup (1 can to 1 small sour cream).
Bake at 275° for 3 hours, uncovered.
Serve with no yolk noodles and cream of mushroom soup or rice.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well and press in greased oblong pan. Mix well remaining ingredients in bowl.
Pour over cake mixture and bake 40 minutes at about 350°.

title: crazy biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk and stir until dough follows fork around bowl.
Knead slightly.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: haystacks
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to a full boil. Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter, then frosted flakes. Spoon onto wax paper.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, cornstarch and enough milk to make a paste. Then add salt to taste and beaten egg yolks.
Mix well, then add remainder of milk.
Add water and vanilla.
Cook until thick.
Add 1/2 stick butter.
Beat until creamy.
Pour in baked pie crust. Add meringue and bake slowly.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, onions, carrot and bell pepper in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with the 3/4 cup sugar.
Mix well.
Let stand while the dressing is prepared.

title: salmon treat
directions: Combine all ingredients as listed and mix.
Place patties in a pan of hot oil and cook.
Your family will be absolutely delighted.

title: hot cocoa
directions: Mix all together and store in air-tight container.
Mix 3 to 4 scoops per cup of boiling water.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Season.
Layer cheese over chicken.
Blend soup and sherry and pour over cheese. Toss stuffing with butter and spoon over all.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake for 15 minutes.
Sauteed fresh mushrooms are a nice addition.

title: cherry jell-o salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl and chill overnight.

title: chicken italiano
directions: In a large shallow baking dish, pour dressing over chicken. Cover and marinate in refrigerator, turning occasionally, for 4 hours or overnight.

title: glazed strawberry tart
directions: Stir together flour, almonds, sugar, lemon rind, and salt in a large bowl.
Cut butter into flour mixture with a pastry blender or 2 knives, until coarse crumbs form.
Whisk together egg and vanilla in a small bowl; stir into flour mixture until a dough forms. Shape into a disk.
Wrap in plastic; refrigerate for at least 1 hour or overnight.

title: fruit trifle
directions: Prepare pudding; stir in flavoring and nutmeg.
Brush cake cubes with juice.
Arrange 1/4 cake on bottom of trifle bowl or other straight sided glass bowl.
Top with 1 cup fruit; spread 1/2 cup pudding on top.
Repeat until cake and all fruit is assembled. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, or until done.

title: quick 'n easy tomato aspic
directions: Mash tomatoes in pan and bring to boil.
Remove from heat. Add Jell-O and softened gelatin.
Stir to dissolve well.
Add olives.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.

title: oatmeal waffles
directions: Stir together flour, oats, baking powder, cinnamon and salt; set aside.
Stir together eggs, milk, butter and brown sugar.
Add to flour mixture; stir until blended.
Pour batter onto grids of preheated waffle iron.
Top with fresh fruit and yogurt.

title: strawberry thing
directions: To create a crust; mix butter, brown sugar, pecans, and flour together.
Press in pan and cook 15 minutes at 350°.
Let Cool.

title: corn light bread
directions: Put sugar, salt, soda and baking powder in bowl.
Mix.
Add buttermilk; stir well.
Add corn meal and flour alternately, mixing after each addition.
Melt shortening in loaf pan.
Add to mixture.
Sprinkle a little corn meal in loaf pan.
Heat pan. Pour mixture into hot pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: lemon fruit slush
directions: Heat and dissolve sugar and water.
Add lemon juice and grated lemon rind.
Freeze in freezer trays and serve over fresh fruit.

title: "low-fat" spiced zucchini bread
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and nuts; set aside.
Beat egg whites lightly in large mixing bowl.
Add sugar, applesauce and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Add dry ingredients, stirring only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter into 2 well-greased and floured (or spray pans with a nonstick spray) 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.
Turn out on rack and cool completely.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Turn dough out on a floured surface; roll dough into a rectangle 1/2-inch thick.
Spread butter over dough, leaving a narrow margin on all sides.
Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over butter.
Sprinkle dough with raisins and pecans, if desired. Tightly roll up jellyroll fashion, beginning on long side.
Pinch edge and ends to seal.
Cut roll into 1-inch slices.
Place slices, cut side down in a greased 9-inch cake pan (fit will be tight).
Cover; let rise in a warm place 45 minutes or until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Store rolls in airtight container.
Yields 1 1/2 dozen.

title: polenta with black beans and salsa
directions: Bring water to a boil; slowly add cornmeal.
Use a whisk to prevent lumping.
Add cumin and pepper.
Reduce the heat and cook, uncovered, for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir often.
When done, polenta should be thick and pull away from the sides of the pan.
Top with black beans (drained) and salsa (recipe follows).

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, then add 3 slightly beaten eggs. Add milk gradually with flour until soft dough forms.
Add vanilla and more flour until thick enough to knead on floured board.
Knead until smooth.
Roll out a portion at a time and cut with any shaped cookie cutter.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: blushing onion soup
directions: In large kettle or Dutch oven, cook onions and garlic in margarine until tender.
Stir in tomato juice, water, bouillon and parsley.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, 20 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Ladle into 8 ovenproof soup bowls.
Top with bread slices and sprinkle generously with cheese. Broil 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve immediately. Makes 8 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli fine, not very much stem.
Fry bacon crisp and crumble.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Toss well together an hour or two before serving.
Chill.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pistachio crumb cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: health club tuna salad
directions: Pour juice from fruit into measuring cup.
Mix in curry powder.
Add enough water to make 2 cups of liquid.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over cracked wheat in bowl; let stand 30 minutes while liquid soaks in and wheat cools.
Mix fruit, tuna, cucumber and green onion.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce.

title: fresh fruit tart
directions: Cream butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat in egg yolk, 1 teaspoon vanilla and almond extracts.
Mix in flour and 1/2 cup almonds to form dough.
Press into an 11-inch tart pan.
Prick shell with fork and bake at 375° until golden, about 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook the noodles according to directions on package. Melt butter in saucepan and stir in flour.
