Add milk, gradually, and cook over low heat until smooth.
Add mushroom soup, tuna, corn, pimentos, onions, 1/3 cup stuffing and spices.
Add 1/2 teaspoon Tabasco sauce.
Stir until heated.
Make two layers of noodles, tuna mixture and cheese in casserole dish. Top with another 1/3 cup of stuffing. Bake in 350° oven until bubbly.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix together.
Place 1/3 cup of mix in mug.
Fill with boiling water.

title: taco dip
directions: Use a 9 x 13 or larger pan.
Let cream cheese warm to room temperature.
Brown hamburger (drain); add beans, taco seasoning and 1 cup of water.
Cook until thick.
Spread cream cheese in pan.
Spread hamburger and bean mixture over cream cheese. Spread 1/2 of Cheddar cheese over mixture.
Spread all sour cream over cheese spread.
Rest of cheese over sour cream.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes; will thicken.
Can be used as a dip or eaten as a main dish.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper and ginger.
Dip chops in flour mixture, shaking off any excess.
In large Dutch oven or deep skillet, heat butter and oil together and brown chops on both sides on high heat.
Add onions and garlic; cook over medium heat until they are soft, about 5 minutes.
Pour off excess accumulated fat in skillet; add beef broth, chili sauce, cider vinegar and brown sugar.
Stir to combine, bring to a boil, cover and simmer slowly for 45 minutes or until chops are tender.
(It may be necessary to add additional beef broth.
Check the liquid level periodically and add broth when necessary.)

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except vanilla.
Boil 1 1/2 minutes, after it comes to a boil.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add vanilla.
Beat with mixer until of spreading consistency.
Enjoy!

title: crab dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill just before serving.

title: cranberry wassail
directions: Simmer in crock-pot for 1 hour.
Serve hot in winter.

title: tomato somerset
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Bake in buttered casserole dish in 300° oven for 45 minutes.

title: hootenanny cake
directions: Grease and flour bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix, vanilla pudding, water, eggs, oil and baking powder for 5 minutes.
In separate bowl, mix nuts, sugar and cinnamon.
Put half of the nut mixture on bottom of pan, then half of cake batter.
Alternate. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Mix and cook ingredients in a crock-pot on low for 8 to 10 hours or high for 4 to 6 hours.
One hour before serving, remove chicken, cool and remove from bone.
Put back and add noodles. Cook on high for 1 hour.

title: apricot cake
directions: Heat pie filling until bubbly.
Grease and flour 9 x 9-inch cake pan.
Put apricots on bottom of cake pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions.
Pour cake mix over apricots.
Sprinkle pecans, coconut and brown sugar over cake mix.
Drizzle oleo over all.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: old-fashioned double-lemon cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt onto piece of wax paper. Set aside. Combine lemon zest and granulated sugar in blender or food processor. Grind until lemon zest is almost as fine as sugar. Cream butter and lemon sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy. Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating until smooth and flowing. Add lemon extract. Mix to combine (curdled appearance is fine). Add sifted dry ingredients. Mix until smooth. Transfer to greased 8 1/2-inch spring-form pan. Smooth surface with spatula. Bake at 325° on center of oven until lightly colored and wood pick inserted in center comes out clean, about 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; fold in sugar gradually.
Add flavoring.
Fold in Rice Krispies and peanut butter.
Thoroughly mix.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove cookies from pan immediately.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: peach pick me up
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender until ice is crushed well.

title: poultry marinade
directions: Boil 3 minutes (not chicken).
Let cool.
Pour over breast or turkey fillets and marinate 3 hours or longer.
Cook on grill until done.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Add vegetables; fry until tender.
Add soups and rice.
Pour into casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix sour cream, spinach, mayo, soup mix and green onions in a bowl. Mix well. Cover and chill for 2 hours. Serve with cut up French bread.

title: butterscotch acorns
directions: Melt butter, remove from heat and stir in sugar, vanilla and pecans.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add to butter mixture. Form dough into 42 balls, using rounded teaspoonful for each. Flatten one end by pressing on ungreased cookie sheet and pinching top to a point to resemble an acorn.
Bake in preheated moderate oven, 350°, for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Melt candy pieces in double-boiler pan.
Dip flat end of cookies into butterscotch to a depth of 1/4-inch.
Thoroughly coat melted candy with nuts.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Beat eggs with milk, salt and mustard.
Brown sausages.
Drain off fat.
Place bread in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, then sausage and then sprinkle with cheese.
Pour egg mixture over bread, sausages and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: german oven pancake
directions: Gradually add flour to eggs, beating with rotary beater.
Stir in milk, melted butter or margarine and salt.
Thoroughly grease a 9 or 10-inch ovenproof skillet.
Pour batter into cold skillet; bake in very hot oven (450°) for about 20 minutes.
Loosen pancake from skillet with wide spatula; cut into wedges.
Serve with syrup.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: homemade egg substitute
directions: Combine all ingredients in electric blender.
Process 30 seconds.
Refrigerate for 1 week.

title: tomorrows salad
directions: Beat
eggs,
add sugar and vinegar.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and marshmallows.
Cool and add fruit and whipped cream.
Let stand for 24 hours.

title: chow mein cookies
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to a good boil.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter.
Add noodles; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: mocha buttercream frosting
directions: Melt and cool chocolate.
Then cream with butter and Crisco. Then add 1/2 of sugar and mix in.
Add egg, vanilla and coffee dissolved in hot water, and mix in.
Then add the rest of the sugar and beat until very smooth and fluffy; several minutes. Frost cake and store in the refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: deluxe pound cake
directions: Cream oleo, Crisco and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add alternately with milk to cream mixture.
Add flavoring.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan or tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked beans
directions: Wash and bake medium to large potatoes, bare-skinned, in oven until done.
Turn once during cooking.
(Cook 1 or 2 more than needed for additional stuffing.)
Cool slightly.
Carefully cut potatoes in half and scoop out of the shells, leaving a thin layer of potato in the shell to give it strength.
Set shells aside.

title: shrimp or tuna salad mold
directions: Sprinkle gelatine
over
water and place on low heat to cook, stirring constantly for about 3 minutes until dissolved. Mix in other
ingredients
in
gelatine mixture and pour into mold. Refrigerate.
Chicken is good, too!

title: turnips
directions: Peel and slice turnips about 1/3-inch thick.
Add seasonings, butter and water.
Cook in covered saucepan until tender, about 45 minutes.
May be cooked in microwave 7 to 8 minutes.

title: apple-chocolate cake
directions: Stir sugar into apples and let stand 15 minutes.
Mix in oil and then eggs.
Mix together flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt and stir into apple mixture.
Add chocolate chips and mix (mixture will be stiff).
Spoon into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 40 minutes in a 350° oven until cake tests done.
Best served warm.

title: california chicken(lenten dish)
directions: Drain water from peas and in it cook carrots, celery and potatoes for 1/2 hour.
Drain tuna fish.
Arrange cooked vegetables in buttered casserole along with peas, tuna fish and crumbs, repeating in layers.
Over all pour the white sauce made from flour, butter and milk.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: turkey meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients except cooking oil and gravy mix.
Mix thoroughly.
Make 1 1/2 or 2-inch meatballs.
In a large saucepan, mix gravy according to package directions.
Add meatballs and simmer for 1 hour and serve with rice or noodles.
Serves 4.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip chicken in mixture of melted butter, pepper sauce and vinegar; put in baking pan.
Sprinkle with 1 package of dry dressing mix.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until browned.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve with celery sticks and Ranch salad dressing as dip.

title: skillet apple potato salad
directions: Wash potatoes; cook in skins in boiling salted water just until tender.
Drain and dice.
Saute bacon in large heavy skillet until crisp.
Add green onion and green pepper; saute until crisp-tender.
Stir in water, vinegar, sugar and seasonings.
Heat to boiling.
Add potatoes and apples to skillet.
Heat thoroughly, stirring gently.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: el dorado beef cheese casserole
directions: This is best when put together the night before serving and refrigerated.

title: fanny farmer fudge
directions: Beat well and pour into greased pan.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° for 30 minutes (until knife comes out clean).
Top with egg white meringue, Cool Whip or whipped cream topping.
This is a real surprise.

title: fiesta cranberry nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add egg and liquid ingredients; beat well.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Fold in cranberry sauce and pecans.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 60 to 65 minutes.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco together; add milk and vanilla. Add sugar 1 cup at a time; mix with mixer until creamy.
More milk may be added to get desired consistency.
Food coloring may be added for decorating.

title: southwest white chili
directions: Heat oil in 2 to 3-quart saucepan over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and cook 4 to 5 minutes, stirring often.
Remove chicken with slotted spoon; cover and keep warm.
Add onion to saucepan and cook 2 minutes.
Stir in next 7 ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in cooked chicken and beans.
Simmer 10 minutes. Garnish with cheese and onions.
Makes 4 servings.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Add 1/2 of dried beef; mix. Roll ball in rest of dried beef.
Refrigerate.

title: green onion dip
directions: In blender or food processor container, place mayonnaise, sour cream, green onions, parsley,
mustard and garlic.
Process until almost smooth.
Cover.
Chill.
Serve with fresh vegetables, crackers or chips.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Boil chicken or use leftover cooked chicken and cut into bite-sized pieces.
Add onion, enchilada sauce, soup, salt and pepper.
Line casserole dish with chips and pour the chicken broth over them.
Top with meat mixture.
Cover with more chips and sprinkle with grated cheese of your choice.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until casserole is bubbly and cheese is melted.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Peel and slice squash.
Cook in boiling water for 5 minutes. Drain; put aside.
Combine soup and sour cream and stir in carrots; fold in squash.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Place cabbage and water in 2-quart saucepan. Cook about 10 minutes over medium heat. Add corned beef and cook until beef is hot and cabbage is tender.

title: chili weather peppers
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Remove tops and seeds from peppers.
Cook 5 minutes in salted boiling water; drain.
Saute onion and celery in butter.
Stir in chili, rice, salt and garlic powder.
Spoon mixture into peppers.
Place stuffed peppers in an 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Top with cheese strips.
Heat 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: ned edwards' reception punch
directions: Serve in punch bowl with ice ring of strawberries.

title: crab newenburg
directions: Saute onion, green pepper, celery, butter, parsley, garlic powder, chives, dry mustard, ginger and cinnamon in a 3-quart saucepan.
Add to sauteed mixture the flour, condensed milk, water, crab, eggs, paprika, salt and pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 10 minutes or until bubbly.
Add soda cracker crumbs.
Turn into rectangle buttered baking dish.
Cook at 350° for 15 to 25 minutes. Serves 6 to 8 people.
Very rich.

title: peach dump cake
directions: Pour peaches in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Place butter over the top of peaches.
Sprinkle cake mix on top of butter and peaches evenly.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: instant spice tea
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in airtight container.
Use 2 or more teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: crisco pound cake
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugar together. Add eggs, one at a time, then lemon flavoring.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt. Alternate, adding dry ingredients with milk.
Mix well and pour into a greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Freezes well.

title: ground beef in gravy
directions: Patty ground beef into about 2-inch patties.
Brown on both sides in a large skillet.
Remove from skillet.
Brown flour in fat; add water slowly, stirring to keep from lumping.
Add milk, salt and pepper, stirring constantly to keep milk from curdling. Add hamburger patties and simmer for about 15 minutes.

title: nancy's quiche
directions: Bake pie crust for 1 minute at 400°.
Mix together the remaining ingredients and pour into pie crust.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
This is so easy and is our favorite quiche.

title: quick chili
directions: Fry hamburger with small onion and chili powder.
Mix chili beans, tomato soup and tomato juice; bring to good boil and serve.

title: coleslaw with dressing
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper in pan. Stir in vinegar gradually.
Add water, mustard and onion.
Cook over medium heat; stir constantly.
Cook until mixture thickens (don't undercook or it will have a starchy taste).
Stir small amount into beaten egg yolks; stir egg yolk mixture into the hot mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes more. Add margarine; stir until thoroughly incorporated.
Chill thoroughly.
Fold in sour cream.
Combine cabbage, carrots and green peppers.
Toss lightly to blend.
Yield:
8 servings. Carbohydrate 10 g, protein 3.4 g, fat 14 g, calories 172.

title: christmas lime sweet pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and slice.
Soak cucumber slices in water and lime mixture, in crockery or enamelware for 24 hours.
Wash 3 times in clean water, removing all lime residue.
Soak in fresh ice water for 3 hours.

title: cranberry pineapple salad
directions: In a bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Break up and stir in cranberry sauce.
Add pineapple, orange juice and lemon juice.
Chill until partially set.
Stir in nuts.

title: blender lemon chess pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender (except shell); blend at medium (whip) speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: In saucepan, cook sliced squash and chopped onion in boiling water for 5 minutes; drain.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Stir in shredded carrots.
Fold in drained squash and onions.
Combine stuffing mix and margarine.
Spread half of stuffing mix in bottom of
12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish (or something similar).
Spoon vegetable mixture on top.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing over vegetables.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 6.

title: "the best" oatmeal cookies
directions: Roll into balls.
Flatten and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: barbecue meat balls(yields 25 to 30)
directions: Mix well and make small balls.
Roll balls in flour and brown in oil.

title: chocolate fudge icing
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, butter and milk to a rolling boil.
Boil for 2 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Beat for 2 1/2 minutes at highest speed.

title: hot water gingerbread
directions: Add boiling water to molasses.
Mix and sift dry ingredients. Add wet mixture to dry.
Add melted fat.
Beat hard.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake in moderate oven (425°) about 25 minutes.

title: hot beef chip dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°. Very good with crackers and chips.

title: pancakes
directions: Combine all the ingredients and stir until well mixed.
If too thick, add a little more milk.
Spoon onto hot griddle and bake until golden on both sides.
Serve hot with butter and syrup of your choice.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in a large bowl, making a well in center of mixture.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour into well.
Stir enough to mix ingredients but do not beat.
Pour batter into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Delicious warm or cold.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: cornbread dressing(low-fat)
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Turn into nonstick baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until light brown and "set."

title: coconut cake
directions: Beat sugar and eggs for 2 minutes, then add softened oleo. Beat until mixed well.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add to mixture.
Stir dry ingredients together and add to mixture along with the vanilla. Cook in three layers at 350°.
Cook until cake springs back in center.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix together ground beef, cracker crumbs, onions, salt and pepper.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight.
Cut in squares.
Flour both sides and brown in a small amount of oil.

title: caramel corn
directions: Heat first 4 ingredients until bubbly.
Cook and stir 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soda.
Put popcorn and syrup in brown paper bag.
Put in microwave and cook 1 minute.
Remove and shake.
Put back in microwave for 1 minute.
Remove and shake. Put back in microwave 1/2 minute and shake.

title: vegetarian swedish meatballs
directions: Form into small balls and fry in hot oil.

title: quiche aux crevettes (shrimp quiche)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Toss the shrimp for 2 minutes in hot butter over moderately high heat.
Season lightly with salt, pepper and herbs.
Add the vermouth and boil rapidly until liquid has almost entirely evaporated.
Spread shrimp in the bottom of your pastry shell.
Beat together the same amount of milk, eggs and seasonings.
Add tomato paste and pour over the shrimp. Spread the grated cheese on top and dot with the butter.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: quick baked pasta (family style)
directions: Put roast in pan, sprinkle with onion salt; add a can of celery soup.
Cover and bake at 325° until tender.

title: smoked sausage appetizer
directions: In skillet, cut up slices of sausage.
Add oil and soy sauce. Fry until brown.
Spread on pan.
While hot, cut pieces of cheese and put on top of sausage.
Ready to serve.

title: squash pickles
directions: Combine squash, peppers, salt and onion. Cover with ice water. Soak 3 hours.
Drain.

title: lady di's cheese rice casserole
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine sour cream, chilies, salt and pepper; mix well.
In buttered casserole dish, layer rice, sour cream mixture and cheese strips.
Top with rice.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese during the last 5 minutes; cook until cheese is melted.

title: peanut butter cookie mix in a jar
directions: Layer ingredients in order given in a 1-quart wide mouth canning jar.
Press each layer firmly in place before adding next layer.

title: homemade pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup water.
Mix flour, sugar and salt in bowl.
Add yeast to flour mixture in bowl.
Knead and shape dough. Brush with egg mixture.
Bake at 420° and eat.

title: chicken chunky style
directions: Cook all ingredients over low heat about 2 1/2 to 3 hours. When chicken is tender, remove from pot and keep warm.
Mix about 3 tablespoons flour with some chicken broth until thin.
Pour flour mixture back into pot and stir until gravy thickens.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: karo nut pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well. Add sugar, salt, Karo syrup and vanilla.
Then melt butter and mix well.
Pour in unbaked crust.
Bake at 350° for first 10 minutes, then at 250° until done or point of knife comes out clean.

title: apple pie(diabetic)
directions: Core and slice apples.
Combine cinnamon and cornstarch and stir into apple juice concentrate.
Heat in pan, stirring until thickened.
Stir in apples, nuts and raisins.
Prepare two 9-inch crusts for pie.
Spoon apple mixture into crust and dot with margarine.
Put on top crusts and cut slits in it.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: potato stuffing
directions: Grind all ingredients except for seasonings.
Add crackers to keep it from getting too moist.
Add seasoning.
Cook slow on low heat, all day is good.
Taste while cooking and add more seasonings as desired.
Add salt and pepper as desired.
Best if made the day before.
Will stuff a small turkey.

title: grilled marinated lamb chops
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients.
Pour marinade over lamb chops and marinate overnight or 5 to 6 hours in covered bowl in refrigerator.
Cook slowly over slow burning fire until center is still slightly pink.
Baste with marinade as often as meat looks dry.
Serves 6.

title: oatmeal carrot cake bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray bottom only of a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray or grease lightly.

title: broccoli-chicken soup
directions: Drain chicken, reserving liquid.
Chop up chicken; set aside. In a 3-quart saucepan, melt butter or margarine; add onion and cook until tender, but not browned.
Stir in flour, dry mustard, salt, thyme and pepper.
Stir in milk and chicken broth all at once.
Cook and stir over medium heat until slightly thickened and bubbly.
Stir in broccoli, chicken and chicken liquid.
Cook and stir for 4 to 6 minutes more or until broccoli is tender and soup is heated through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: coke salad
directions: Stir together the first 3 ingredients and bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from
heat and add the jello slowly.
Add Coke.
Mix and let stand 10 minutes, then add crushed pineapple and nuts.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: sun-maid raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Wash raisins in hot water and drain.
Cream shortening with sugar, then add beaten eggs and milk.
Combine with oatmeal and raisins and mix well.
Add flour sifted with baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Beat thoroughly.
Drop by tablespoon onto greased pans and bake in moderate oven (350° to 375°) for about 12 minutes. Makes about 3 dozen medium-sized cookies.
Store between layers of wax paper.

title: nut balls
directions: Combine these ingredients and form into balls; coat with confectioners sugar.
Make balls about 1 inch in size.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in 300° oven.
When cool, roll again in sugar.

title: orange wafer balls
directions: Crush vanilla wafers into fine crumbs; add sugar, nuts, margarine and orange juice.
Mix well and shape into bite-sized balls.
Roll lightly in coconut.
Chill and place in an airtight container.
Store in refrigerator.
Yields 5 or 6 dozen.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cut shrimp into small pieces.
Add cream cheese, onion and mayonnaise.
Add Worcestershire sauce to taste. Chill.

title: eagle brand milk(sweetened condensed milk)
directions: Place margarine and water in blender.
Mix well with milk and sugar.
Add to water and margarine.
Blend until smooth.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Melt for 5 min. Add pecans & coat. Bake at 350° for 15 min.

title: asparagus with brown butter
directions: Wash and trim vegetables. Cook in boiling salted water 8 to 12 minutes. Drain and keep warm. Melt butter in small saucepan or frying pan over medium heat. Add almonds. Cook and stir until butter and almonds are golden brown, 1 to 2 minutes. Add lemon juice, salt and pepper. Spoon over hot asparagus. Makes 6 to 8 servings. Broccoli may also be used.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Put chili sauce and jelly in slow cooker.
Add wieners and simmer 2 hours.

title: wilted spinach salad
directions: Fry bacon; remove from skillet.
Add onions to drippings. Soften over medium heat.
Add remaining ingredients (except spinach).
Place spinach in large bowl.
Pour hot dressing over spinach.
Add crumpled bacon and chopped egg; toss lightly and serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water until tender and drain. Melt margarine; blend in flour. Add milk. Cook and stir until thick. Add cheese and pepper. Stir until melted. Mix sauce with macaroni. Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes until bubbly and browned. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: peach cobbler pie
directions: Put 1 stick margarine in 9 x 13-inch baking dish to melt.
Mix 1 1/2 cups self-rising flour with 1/2 cup shortening and 1/3 cup milk.
Roll out; put 2 cups of fruit on dough.
Roll up like jelly roll and cut up.
Put fruit and dough in melted margarine.
Heat 2 cups sugar and 2 cups juice or water.
Pour over dough.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: jiffy rolls or bread
directions: Mix cake mix and yeast together and set aside.
Mix water and salt together in large bowl.
Stir in yeast mixture and 3 cups flour.
Knead about 6 minutes.
Cover and let rise 1 hour.
Punch down and make into 24 rolls or 2 loaves bread.
Let rise and bake at 350° to 375° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: big red meat loaf
directions: Combine ground beef, oatmeal, onion, green pepper, parsley, mustard, salt, marjoram, pepper, eggs and milk in large bowl.
Mix lightly, but well.
Press mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread with Piquant Sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Saute chicken, onion and garlic in butter until chicken browns, about 5 minutes.
Stir in cornstarch; cook 1 minute.
Add broth, carrot, lemon juice, lemon peel and salt.
Bring to a boil. Stir in pea pods, parsley and rice.
Cover, remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Serves 4.

title: german pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well, then mix with remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly, then pour into unbaked pie shell.
Begin baking at 350° for 15 minutes, then reduce to 250°.
Bake for about 1 hour until done.

title: date nut bread
directions: Cream thoroughly the sugar, shortening, egg and vanilla.
Add date mixture, stir and mix, then add flour, soda and nuts.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients 3 minutes.
Add vanilla and strawberries to the boiled sugar, water and lemon juice and stir. Pour into a container and store in the refrigerator overnight. Just before serving, add club soda and ginger ale.
(If you use frozen strawberries, thaw partially and put in a blender to crush.)

title: skillet cookies
directions: Cook in a heavy skillet over low flame until dates dissolve. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla, 2 1/2 cups Rice Krispies and 1 cup chopped pecans.
Shape into balls.
Roll in coconut.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bacon.
Turn into a 14 x 10 x 2-inch pan.
Bury bacon in beans and bake, uncovered, in a 300° oven for 2 hours.
Bring bacon to top and bake for 30 minutes more.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.
Serves a lot.

title: rich frosted brownies
directions: Combine
sugar, flour, eggs, oleo, cocoa and vanilla in a large
mixing bowl.
Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed with electric mixer.
Stir
in nuts.
Pour into well greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch
baking
pan.
Bake	at
325° for 30 minutes or until center
is	firm.
Allow to cool.
Frost with Chocolate Frosting.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan.
Heat until red hots melt. Pour into one-gallon pitcher.
Finish filling pitcher with water. Reheat or serve cold.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix together in an ovenproof dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly. Serve with crackers. Serves 10.

title: lemon pie made e z
directions: Squeeze lemons (remove seeds) and add to Cool Whip.
Add milk. Place in pie shells and chill.

title: sloppy chicken
directions: Steam chicken in enough water to cover.
Cook until done. (Place onion with chicken for flavor.)
When done, remove from pan and strain juice.
Pull chicken off bone.
Set aside.
Add a can of chicken broth to juice.
Mix cornstarch with water.
Add to broth and simmer until thickened.
Serve over rice.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Add milk.
Add baking soda. Mix thoroughly.
Add crushed bananas.
Slowly add flour, salt and nuts.
Pour into a well-greased bread pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix all together as usual, roll out and cut in pieces.
Dip in melted butter.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: new orleans red beans and rice
directions: Rinse kidney beans twice.
Discard any that look bad.
Put beans in a big, heavy pot, at least 3-quart size (4-quart is better).
Add water, ham and sausage.
Set, uncovered, on a burner at medium heat.
While beans are soaking and warming, chop and add scallions, green pepper, celery and onions.
Then add thyme and bay leaves.
When mixture boils, reduce heat and cover.
Stir every 20 to 30 minutes for three hours.
Then with a wooden spoon, mash about 1/4 of the beans against the side of the pot.
If they don't mash easily, try again after half an hour.
Forty minutes after mashing the beans, taste and season with cayenne pepper or Tabasco sauce.
(Don't use too much.
This is supposed to be delicious, but subtly flavored.)
Cook for another half hour while preparing rice.
Ladle beans and sauce over rice and serve.
It's hard to believe, but all the vegetables cook away to nothing.
The mashed beans thicken the sauce to a creamy consistency.
It's even more flavorful rewarmed after a night in the fridge.

title: batter fried chicken
directions: Combine egg, milk and oil.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and pepper.
Add to milk mixture.
Beat until smooth. Dip chicken into batter.
Drain 5 to 10 minutes on wire rack. Fill skillet or Dutch oven 1/2 full with oil.
Heat to 375°.
Cook chicken about 10 to 15 minutes or until done.
Drain on paper towels.

title: dill potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender; drain and cut into slices or cubes.
In a bowl, combine sour cream, onion and dill and blend well.
Pour over warm potatoes and toss gently to mix thoroughly.

title: apple brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except for apples and nuts. Then add the apples and nuts to mixture.
(If using McIntosh apples, add an extra 1/2 to 2/3 cup flour.)
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Test with toothpick.

title: hamburg and rice casserole
directions: Fry hamburger, celery and onion until brown.
Mix together in baking dish. Bake 2 hours at 350° or 3 hours at 300°.

title: calabacita
directions: Place zucchini and corn in a steamer basket.
Place over but not touching boiling water.
Cover and reduce heat; cook 15 minutes.
In saucepan, cook green onions and garlic in oil until tender, but not brown.
In 2-quart casserole combine cooked vegetables, tomatoes, oregano and thyme.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven about 15 minutes or until heated through, stirring once.
Stir in the cheeses just before serving.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel apples and slice thin.
Place in a greased baking dish. Combine all other ingredients with a pastry blender.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: lazy chicken cordon bleu
directions: Remove bones and cut chicken into bite size pieces.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, place chicken on bottom with ham on top. Sprinkle some cheese on top.
Mix together soup, water, onion and parsley.
Pour soup mix over chicken, ham and cheese.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and golden brown. Goes well with boiled potatoes, green beans and salad.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Crumble bacon in crust.
Cover with cheese and onion rings. Mix flour, salt and pepper; blend with milk.
Add eggs to mixture and beat.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until fork inserted in center comes out clean.
To prevent overbaking of crust, rub butter on edges before baking and lay foil loosely over top during latter baking time, if necessary.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: black bing cherry salad
directions: Mix juice from one of the cans of cherries, sherry wine, 1 1/2 cups of orange juice and 1 cup sugar and bring to a boil. Dissolve Knox gelatine in 1/2 cup orange juice.
Pour hot mixture over gelatine and when it's partially set, put cherries stuffed with pecans or almonds in hot juice.
Mold in large ring or individual molds.

title: rice salad
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni according to directions using half the butter.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients and chill several hours or overnight.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and molasses; beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Bake in greased shallow pan in moderate oven (350°) for 45 minutes.

title: green tomato jelly
directions: Boil the sugar and tomatoes for 7 minutes.
Add the jello to the boiling mixture and dissolve completely.
Pour into prepared jars.

title: never fail michigan pot roast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rub roast with crushed garlic.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mince garlic and set aside.
Heat butter and oil in large Dutch oven over medium heat.
Add meat and brown well 2 minutes per side.
Transfer to a plate.
Add onions and garlic to pot and cook 3 minutes.
Stir in chicken broth, scraping bottom and sides of pot.
Return meat to pot and heat to boiling.
Cover and bake 1 hour and 40 minutes.
Add potatoes and carrots and bake 1 hour more.
Make gravy from broth after removing meat and vegetables.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Heat a nonstick skillet and spray with vegetable oil cooking spray. Add the chicken, onions and garlic. Cook, stirring frequently until the chicken is golden and cooked through, about 10 minutes. Remove the skillet from the heat and set aside.

title: seafood dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and keep refrigerated until ready to use. The onion soup mix is to be added as to your own taste.

title: braised meat
directions: Take a sufficient portion of meat suitable for the number to be served.
(Short ribs of beef, oxtails, veal shanks or liver cut 1 1/2-inches thick.)
Cut meat in servicing size pieces and dredge with flour.
Brown well in heavy skillet; season with salt and pepper (herbs, if you like them).
Slice onions over top and add enough hot water to cover meat.
Simmer for about 1 1/2 hours. Veal and liver cook faster than beef.
I do not add any more water but turn the meat several times.
After cooking take the meat out and thicken gravy a little and add about 1/2 cup water.
Gravy may be poured over meat or served separately.

title: white icing
directions: Beat 4 egg whites until stiff in a bowl.
In a pan, put 2 cups sugar and 1/2 cup water; bring to a boil.
Add 1 tablespoon vinegar.
Boil until it spins a 3 to 4 inch thread.
Beat egg whites while pouring hot sugar syrup over them, then beat in 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until cool.
Spread over cake.

title: irene's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, spices and marshmallows in double boiler until marshmallows melt.
Cool.
Add the whipped cream a little at a time.
Put in baked pie shell.
Cover with finely chopped pecans. Place in refrigerator a couple hours before cutting.

title: punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; place in container and freeze.
To serve, let thaw for 2 hours.
Add ginger ale.
Chop and serve.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together well and form small balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, turning 1 or 2 times.

title: broiled bluefish
directions: Place fish in foil-lined pan, skin side up.
Baste with a mixture of melted shortening, salt, lemon juice and pepper. Sprinkle each piece with paprika.
Place pan 4 to 5 inches from broiler unit and cook 5 minutes.
Turn fish and repeat basting and paprika.
Cook about 5 more minutes or until fish flakes easily. Serves 4.

title: hot beef sandwiches
directions: Put into crock-pot for 6 hours. Great for a crowd. Great on hard rolls.

title: sugar-free muffins
directions: In saucepan, combine dates, raisins, prunes and water.
Bring to a boil and boil 5 minutes.
Set aside and cool.
Add remaining ingredients to fruit.
Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Put in muffin tin.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. (Bake in pan 30 minutes.)

title: angel food pie
directions: Boil cornstarch, sugar and water until thick; add salt.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Slowly pour boiled mixture into egg whites, beating constantly.
Add vanilla and pineapple.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip and nuts.

title: salmon pate
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
In a small bowl, combine salmon with cream cheese, lemon juice, 4 tablespoons chopped parsley and remaining ingredients except almonds.
Chill until firm enough to shape.
Mold salmon into fish on platter.
Arrange almonds on top of fish to resemble scales.
Garnish with parsley.
Chill for several hours to blend flavors.
Serve with crackers or vegetable sticks.

title: peach parfait pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Add peaches to jello.
Melt ice cream enough so it can be whipped into thick cream.
Add to jello mixture.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish. Mix sugar and flour, then add milk and stir until well mixed. Pour this mixture over melted butter in baking dish. Pour peaches over top of all this. Do not stir. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well and shape into 2 rolls.
Place in wax paper in refrigerator.
When chilled, slice and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken waldorf salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sugar and lemon juice in a bowl.
Cut half the apple into slices.
Dip in additional lemon juice and set aside.
Dice remaining apple.
Stir diced apple, chicken, celery and 3 tablespoons of coconut
into mayonnaise mixture.
Serve on crisp spinach leaves.
Garnish with carrot sticks, apple slices and remaining coconut.
Makes 1 1/2 cups or 1 serving.

title: fried mushroom nuggets
directions: Rinse mushrooms and pat dry with paper towel.
In a bowl, blend the flour, garlic powder and club soda until smooth.
Dip mushrooms in batter and fry in about 1-inch of oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels before serving.

title: savory scrambled eggs
directions: Melt margarine in skillet over low heat.
Add combined eggs, milk and seasonings; cook slowly, stirring until eggs begin to set.
Add cream cheese; continue cooking, stirring occasionally until cream cheese is melted and eggs are cooked.
Garnish with green onion slices and sprinkle with paprika if desired.

title: pumpkin tea bread
directions: Combine sugar and oil, blending well; add eggs and beat until light and creamy.
Stir in pumpkin.
Combine remaining ingredients; add to creamed mixture and beat until well blended. Pour into 3 greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 5/8-inch loaf pans (or two 9-inch loaf pans).
Bake at 325°
for 1 hour or until lightly browned.
Cool 15 minutes in pans; remove from pans and cool completely on rack.
Bread freezes very well.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water in mixing bowl. Add sugar, oil and egg. Stir to dissolve sugar. Mix in 1 cup of the flour until smooth.
Place over pan of hot water.
Cover with towel and let it rise 15 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together and store in airtight container.
To make hot chocolate, use 1/3 cup of mix for each cup of water.

title: cora's jumbo cookies
directions: Bring raisins and water to a boil for 3 minutes.
Let cool. Mix remaining ingredients.
Drop on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Soak broccoli and cauliflower in ice water for 15 minutes. Drain and pour on dressing made from remaining ingredients.
Toss to mix thoroughly.

title: onion casserole
directions: Cook onions in butter until transparent; do not brown.
Add half and half, rice and cheese.
Mix well and pour into slightly buttered, 2-quart oblong dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: poor man supper #2
directions: Brown hot link slices.
Add all ingredients except rice. Cover with lid.
Cook over medium-low until corn is cooked. Serve over rice.

title: applesauce raisin cookies
directions: Simmer raisins in water until water is absorbed.
Add applesauce, vanilla, oil, sweetener and eggs to cooled raisins. Stir in dry ingredients and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased baking sheets and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, just until done.
Do not overbake.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; set aside.
Combine dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Add Crisco.
Add buttermilk and yeast mixture, mixing well until dough forms a ball.
Cover bowl and chill overnight.

title: chocolate peanut buddy bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl beat peanut butter and butter until smooth.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Blend in flour and salt.
Stir in 1 cup chocolate morsels.
Spread into ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until edges begin to brown.
Immediately sprinkle remaining chocolate morsels on top.
Let stand 5 minutes until morsels become shiny and soft.
Spread morsels evenly over top. Cool completely.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch bars.
Makes 48 bars.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Chop onion and broccoli.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Blend dry instant pudding into whipped topping and mix well. Add crushed pineapple along with its juices.
Fold in marshmallows and nuts.
Refrigerate about 2 hours.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Heat butter and olive oil in large skillet.
Add shrimp and saute until done (about 5 minutes).
Add remaining ingredients. Cook another minute.
French bread is great for capturing all the juices.
Good served with rice or fettucini.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Line a buttered casserole dish with sliced carrots.
Pour drained broccoli on top of carrots.
Cover with cheese and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: tuna skillet royale
directions: In a large (10-inch) frypan, saute the celery and garlic in butter.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Cook spaghetti per package directions and drain.
Add to mixture.
Simmer slowly for about 10 minutes or until heated thoroughly.
Serves 4.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: In a large saucepan, combine first 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil over medium heat for 30 seconds.
Stir in quickly the last 3 ingredients.
After mixing, drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper. Cool. Cookies become firm.

title: orange-date cake
directions: Pour over cake as soon as cake is taken from oven.

title: spice tea
directions: Let all ingredients come to a boil.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes; remove cloves.

title: peanut patties
directions: Put
first 3 ingredients in a large pan and cook slowly until it	forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Take off fire and add butter, powdered sugar and red food coloring. Stir	until it	begins	to thicken.
Drop by big spoonfuls on waxed paper. (Allow plenty of room to spread.)

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Cover with topping.
Bake for about 35 minutes at 350°.

title: breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Mix with cream cheese.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, place 1 package rolls on bottom; top with "goop".
Place second package of rolls on top.
Bake at crescent roll package directions until brown.
"Great with omelets."

title: white lasagne
directions: Cook lasagne noodles.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Saute celery, onion and garlic in ground beef.
Add basil, salt, Italian seasoning, oregano and black pepper.
Stir.
Next stir in light cream, cream cheese and white wine.
Add Gouda, cottage cheese, egg, Mozzarella cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Mix all ingredients over low heat until smooth and creamy.
Grease lasagne pan and layer, starting with lasagne, sauce, lasagne, etc.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.
Makes 8 servings.

title: susan boswell's chocolate eclair cake
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk.
Mix well.
Fold in frozen whipped topping and beat for 2 minutes at medium speed.

title: cheese soup
directions: In saucepan, mix carrots, onions, celery and chicken broth. Heat to boiling; reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Combine milk, flour and salt.
Stir into broth mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Add cheese, stirring until melted.
Serves 4.

title: belle's hawaiian country ham
directions: Place ham slices in skillet.
Cover with cold water and heat to boiling point.
Do not boil.
Pour off water.
Place slices flat in baking pan or Corning dish.
Add 2 ounces water per slice and place in preheated oven (375°).
Turn ham (add water when necessary) until both sides are slightly brown.
Reduce heat to 300°.
Add sugar to pineapple juice to make very sweet and pour (4 ounces per slice) over ham.
Cover with utensil cover or aluminum foil.
Cook 45 minutes or until tender and sauce begins to thicken.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cover bottom of pan with broccoli, then chicken.
Combine soup, mayo and lemon juice.
Pour on top of broccoli and chicken. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Top with buttered bread cubes.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Use a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: sweet potatoes royale
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Spoon into lightly greased 12 x 18 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Coconut can be mixed in with first 5 ingredients or be sprinkled on top.
Top with marshmallows and bake 15 minutes more.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar together until light. Add the eggs and beat until well mixed.
Add the flour and baking powder.
Gradually add the milk, beating until mixture is smooth. Fold in the blueberries.
Pour into greased muffin tins.
Fill about 1/2 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen muffins.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Bake cake according to package directions; cool.
Prepare pudding according to package directions; set aside.
Crumble cake; reserve 1/2 cup.
Place half of remaining cake crumbs in the bottom of a trifle dish or decorated glass bowl.
Layer with 1/2 the coffee, 1/2 the pudding, 1/2 the whipped topping and 1/2 the crushed candy bars.
Repeat layers.
Combine remaining crushed candy bars with reserved cake crumbs; sprinkle over top. Refrigerate 4 to 5 hours.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: crescent cookies
directions: Cream the butter, sugar, vanilla and water; add flour and salt.
Mix in nuts.
Roll into crescent shape.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Let cool.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl and shape into balls. Refrigerate overnight.
Melt chocolate chips with 1/3 bar paraffin wax on low heat.
Dip balls in chocolate and lay on wax paper. Refrigerate.

title: marshmallows
directions: Sift cornstarch and powdered sugar together. Grease 8 x 8-inch pan and scatter a spoonful sifted mixture all over the pan to coat it. Save the rest for the end. Sprinkle gelatin into the water in a small pan and stir over low heat until dissolved. Add the gelatin water to the remaining ingredients (except sugar mix) in a large mixing bowl and beat until stiff peaks form, about 15 to 20 minutes. Smooth this fluffy mix into square pan and set aside for 3 hours. When set, cut into squares. Sprinkle the remaining sugar/starch mix onto the counter and flip over the pan. Tumble the cubes in the sugar mix to coat on all sides. Let dry overnight. Enjoy with hot chocolate or store in airtight container.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix milk, vanilla and margarine into confectioners sugar. Mix until smooth dough forms.
Add more confectioners sugar as needed.
Dough should not be sticky.
Lay a piece of wax paper on table to roll dough on.
Divide dough into thirds.
Roll one section of dough at a time.
It should be no thicker than 1/4 inch thick.
Spread 1/3 of the peanut butter on thickly, adjust thickness of peanut butter to own preference.
Roll up in log type shape.
Wrap with Saran Wrap and refrigerate.
After chilled, cut into 1/2 inch thick slices and serve.
Can be stored in refrigerator.

title: parker house rolls
directions: Scald milk and cool. When lukewarm, add potato and potato water. Add salt, sugar, shortening and egg to the liquid; add yeast which was dissolved in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Put flour in pan and make a well in center; add liquids and mix until dough can be kneaded. Knead until dough is smooth and no longer sticky. Cover and let rise until doubled.
Roll out to 3/4 inch thick. Grease 1/2 of dough and fold over ungreased half; cut with biscuit cutter. Put in greased pans and let rise until doubled. Bake in hot oven at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over sugar, salt, shortening and mashed potatoes.
Stir until shortening is dissolved and mixture cools. Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water; add to the mixture.
Mix well then stir in flour to make a soft dough.
Rub bowl with shortening, cover tightly.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: blueberry velvet pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, condensed milk, Cool Whip and frozen lemonade together. Pour into graham cracker crust. Chill in the refrigerator for 2 hours. Remove and pour on blueberry filling. Return to the refrigerator for 2 more hours.

title: hello dolly bars
directions: Melt margarine in an 8 x 8 x 2 pan. Next sprinkle in layers: graham cracker crumbs, coconut, chocolate chips, and pecans. Pour the sweetened milk over all. Bake at 350 degree for 30-35 minutes.

title: creme de menthe brownies
directions: Beat together ingredients up to and including chocolate syrup. Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Beat powdered sugar, creme de menthe and 1/2 cup butter.
Spread over cake and set 5 minutes.
Melt chocolate chips and 6 tablespoons butter.
Cool, then spread on cake.

title: corn-cheese spoonbread
directions: Combine eggs, corn, butter, cornbread mix and baking powder in large bowl.
Pour mixture into lightly greased 2-quart casserole. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle top with cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: sweet potato slaw
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, apple, raisins and nuts in a large bowl; stir well.
Blend yogurt, mayonnaise, orange rind and apple jelly.
Pour over sweet potato mixture.
Cover and chill.
Serve, garnished with miniature marshmallows if desired.

title: chocolate crackles
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, water and shortening.
Mix with a spoon
until
well blended.
Shape dough into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll
balls
in powdered sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake
at
for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: kentucky hot brown
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add flour, stir well.
Add milk, cheeses and seasonings.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick. Arrange turkey on toast and cover with cheese sauce.
Top
with tomato and bacon.
Sprinkle with 4 ounces Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 425° until bubbly.
Serves 4.

title: chicken breast diane
directions: Place chicken breasts between sheet of waxed paper and pound slightly.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Heat 1 tablespoon each of oil and butter in large skillet.
Cook chicken 4 minutes on each side.
Do not overcook or they will be dry.
Transfer to warm platter.
Add green onion and lemon juice and mustard to skillet. Cook 15 seconds, whisking constantly.
Whisk in broth.
Stir until sauce is smooth.
Whisk in remaining butter and oil.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Serve immediately.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup and mayo together. Lay chicken and vegetables in 9 x 13 pan. Cover with soup mixture. Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese and buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 375° about 1 hour, until chicken is tender.

title: walnut wafers
directions: Mix brown sugar and eggs.
Beat and then add other ingredients.
Drop on buttered cookie sheet with a teaspoon. Bake in a moderate oven for 8 to 12 minutes.
Yields 3 to 4 dozen.

title: almond wild rice
directions: Saute rice, onion and almonds in butter 5 minutes or until almonds are browned.
Stir in water and bouillon granules.
Pour into an ungreased 10 cup casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Cream butter in a large mixing bowl at high speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Gradually add sugar; continue creaming at high speed until light and fluffy.
By hand, stir in flour, frosting mix and walnuts until well blended.
Pour batter into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes. Cool completely before serving.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Put ingredients in mixing bowl.
Microwave for three minutes. Beat with portable mixer, spoon or kitchen mixer for about two minutes; add nuts if desired.
Put mixture onto greased pan and place in freezer for about 30 minutes.

title: cream puffs
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, heat water, butter and salt until butter melts and mixture boils.
Remove from heat.
With wooden spoon stir in flour all at once until mixture forms a ball and leaves sides of saucepan.
Add eggs, one at a time beating after each slightly.
Lightly grease and flour cookie sheet.
Drop by heaping Tbsp.
Bake for 40 min.
Turn off oven and leave in oven for 15 min.
Fill each puff with almond-cream filling then glaze each puff.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onion until done in saucepan with enough water to cover.
Mix milk and flour until all flour lumps are dissolved; add to potatoes and onion.
Cook until slightly thick. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: cranberry pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in oil in a large skillet; drain pan drippings.
Sprinkle pork chops with salt and pepper.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Set pineapple aside.
Combine juice, 1/2 cup hot water and next 4 ingredients.
Pour over pork chops. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Place pineapple slices and pepper rings on top of pork chops; cover and simmer an additional 10 minutes.
Transfer chops, pineapple and pepper rings to a serving platter, reserving the pan drippings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook onion in butter. Add cheese and soup. Cook until melted. Add rice and broccoli. Pour into dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes uncovered.

title: biscuit rolls
directions: Mix 2 cups flour with shortening, then add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut tops from green peppers, discard seeds and chop enough of the tops to make 1/4 c.
Set aside.
Cook whole peppers uncovered in boiling water 5 minutes, invert, drain and sprinkle insides with salt.
In skillet, cook beef, onion and 1/4 c. chopped green peppers until meat is brown and veggies are tender.
Drain off excess fat and add tomatoes with juice, uncooked rice, water, salt, Worcestershire sauce and a dash of pepper.
Bring to boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer 15-18 minutes until rice is tender. Stir in cheese.
Stuff peppers with meat mixture.
Place in baking dish and bake covered at 350 degrees for 30-35 minutes.

title: maria's homemade tortillas
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut shortening into mix.
Add water slowly; pour a little, then stir, pour, then stir.
Sprinkle in more flour if too sticky.
You need to have consistency of bread dough.
Knead 5 minutes.
Pinch off a large ball.
Form into large, round biscuit size mound 1/2-inch thick and 2-inches around.
Continue to make rounds until all dough is used.
Roll each to form flat pancake.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Add 1 cup water to zucchini. Bring to a boil. Cook 6 minutes. Add sugar, lemon juice, pineapple and jello. Cook 6 minutes more. Put in jars.

title: coconut meringue pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Cook for 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Stir small amount of hot mixture into egg yolks.
Return to hot mixture.
Cook 2 minutes. Remove from heat; add 1 cup coconut, butter and vanilla.
Pour into pie crust.

title: sweet and sour punch
directions: Mix all ingredients for concentrate. Make punch 1 part concentrate to 3 parts water.

title: stuffed peppers salad style
directions: Remove cap and seeds from bell pepper.
Mix tuna, rice and mayonnaise to desired consistency.
Add salt or lemon pepper, celery salt, whatever tastes good.
Stuff pepper and enjoy.
May be chilled, if you prefer.
Serves one.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: On a large plate or platter, layer the dip first, then avocados mashed or blended with lemon juice, salt and pepper, then sour cream mixed with mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
Layer the onions, tomatoes, olives, then cheese.

title: fresh cranberry-raisin pie
directions: Put bottom crust in a 9-inch pie plate.
Refrigerate with rest of pastry until ready to fill.
Combine all ingredients, except butter and egg.
Bring to a boil over medium heat until cranberries start to pop.

title: butternut squash soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook onion and ginger in butter until soft. Add chicken broth, water, garlic and squash. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Puree in blender. Add lime juice, salt and pepper. Reheat over low heat.

title: grandma's orange cupcakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together; spoon into a mini cupcake pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: jumbo stuffed shrimp
directions: Preheat oven to 425° (220° C).
In 2 tablespoons of butter, saute the onion.
Blend in the mustard and sage.
Remove from heat. In mixing bowl, blend together the bread crumbs, crab meat, egg, cream, sage mixture and remaining butter.
Place 2 teaspoons of mixture on each butterflied shrimp.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot.
Garnish with sprig of fresh dill or mint and lemon twist. Serves 4.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a saucepan; heat until shortening melts, stirring occasionally.
Cool mixture to 105° to 115°.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Line cake pan with hash browns; bake at 375° for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Put a layer of the prepared hamburger mix, a layer of cheese and onions, another layer of hamburger mix and layer of cheese and onions.
Put back in oven for about 1/2 hour.

title: barley casserole
directions: Saute onion and barley until brown.
Add other ingredients. Bake in a greased casserole for 2 1/2 hours at 350°.
Can use a slow cooker.

title: bachelor quick supper
directions: Cook or steam cauliflower and cut up in small florets.
In pie dish, spread oil or spray and lay slices of cheese on the dish so it covers the bottom as a pie crust.
Put cooked, drained cauliflower in dish.
Add the butter, salt and pepper.
Put second package of cheese on top, covering like a crust.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Place in 400° oven for 20 minutes (until cheese begins to brown).
Take from oven and let stand for 5 minutes. You can use a small head of cauliflower and 1 pkg. of cheese. Split the cheese for two layers and use 1/4 cup of breadcrumbs.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water (you can microwave also).
Peel and dice.
Add vinegar and seasoning.
Fry bacon until crisp. Combine potatoes, chopped eggs, drained and crumbled bacon, 2 tablespoons bacon fat and chopped onion.
Mix well.
Serve hot salad on bed of lettuce.

title: new england corn chowder
directions: Cook onions and potatoes in water.
Add corn and 1 can milk. Add butter or margarine.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: cacahuetes endadiablados(deviled peanuts)
directions: In mixing bowl combine peanuts, oil, chili powder, salt and cayenne.
Spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a
350° oven
for	30
minutes
or
until peanuts are lightly browned, shaking pan occasionally.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Spread pineapple in casserole dish.
Mix Cheddar cheese, sugar and flour.
Spread mixture over top of pineapple.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Melt oleo.
Pour over Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Delicious.

title: pecan roll
directions: Boil the water and syrup to hard ball stage (248°).
Take from fire and add the Pet milk.
Add the butter. Cook to soft ball (238°).
Stir constantly.
Add pecans and vanilla. Beat and then roll. To roll, butter a large sheet of waxed paper.
Pour the candy on it and roll up with your hands. Grease hands with more butter.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Prepare butter cake as directed.
Blend cream cheese, confectioners sugar, sugar and butter.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Slice cake horizontally.
Frost the first two layers with filling and then put half of the pie filling on the top of
the two layers. Frost the other two layers with the filling.
Add rest of pie filling to top of cake.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Bring water to a boil. Add sugar and syrup.
Stir until dissolved and boil until it reaches 280°.
Add peanuts.
Cook slowly over low heat and add butter, soda and vanilla.
Stir quickly and spread on large buttered pan.
Put in a cold area. When cooled, break in pieces.

title: paula's wedding punch
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Melt margarine in pan. Add mix and 2 eggs in pan. Stir together. Spread evenly in pan.
Mix the cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar (minus a dab for top of cake after baking).
Mix together and spread over other mixture. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Chop cranberries and put in a bowl.
Add sugar; let set overnight in refrigerator.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Prepare Dream Whip as directions show.
Fold into cranberries, then fold in 1/2 package of marshmallows.
Chill 1 hour.

title: zucchini-carrot au gratin
directions: In a large saucepan, cover carrots with water.
Bring water to a boil and cook carrots about 3 to 5 minutes or until just tender; drain.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Place zucchini in a greased 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Place carrots over zucchini.
Place pieces of butter evenly over carrots.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and cheese evenly over vegetables.
Pour chicken broth evenly over top.
Cover and bake 20 minutes.
Bake uncovered 25 to 30 minutes longer or until cheese browns and vegetables are tender.
This freezes well.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water; add 7 to 10 ice cubes. Remove when jello thickens.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill for 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: coconut cream pie filling
directions: In double boiler, scald milk.
Mix sugar, salt, cornstarch and egg yolks.
Pour some of the milk into this mixture and beat good. Then add to scalding milk.
Stir constantly; add vanilla.
When thick, remove and cool.
Sprinkle coconut in pie shell and add filling.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl, stir together all ingredients but pecans. Stir until well blended.
Pour into pie shell. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool.

title: mexican rice
directions: Cook rice according to package directions, salt included. Meanwhile, saute onion, pepper and garlic in vegetable oil until golden, stirring often and taking care not to burn.
When rice is done, add rice to cooked vegetables.
Stir and heat over medium-high heat.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add 1 to 2 teaspoons chili powder and about 1/2 cup salsa.
Stir until blended well and salsa is absorbed into rice.

title: apple brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except apples.
Blend well. (Mixture will be thick.)
Add apples.
Spray with Pam a 9 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: calico baked beans
directions: Fry bacon, ground beef and onion together; drain off fat.
Mix in catsup, sugar, brown sugar, mustard, salt and vinegar.
Add beans.
Bake in 3-quart casserole at 300° about 1 hour.

title: pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill.
Garnish with crisp-cooked bacon that has been crumbled.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, celery and water chestnuts.
Combine next 6 ingredients and stir well.
Add to chicken mixture and toss well. Chill.
Sprinkle with toasted almonds.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: prize winning meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl. Press ingredients into an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour. Drain; let stand 5 minutes.

title: brandy beans
directions: Saute meat and chopped onion.
Combine with chili sauce or catsup and mix well.
Alternate layers of beans and meat mixture in baking dish.
Pour coffee and then brandy on top (do not mix). Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, uncovered, until bubbly and brown.

title: new york style cheese cake
directions: Let cream cheese, sour cream, butter and eggs stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Blend the cream cheese, sour cream and butter together, then add cornstarch, sugar, vanilla and lemon juice.
Beat at whip speed until blended well.
Beat in one egg at a time until mixture is smooth.
Pour into greased 9 1/2-inch spring-form pan.
Place pan in a large roasting pan filled with warm water.
Bake in 375° oven for 1 hour or until top is golden brown.
Turn off oven.
Let cake cool 2 hours in oven.
Remove from roasting pan, cover and refrigerate for at least 6 hours. Remove spring-form pan.
Slice and serve.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Brown ground beef and onion together, then add salt, chili powder, garlic, salt, sugar, tomato paste, tomato sauce, water and oregano. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Place 3 to 4 uncooked noodles in bottom of pan.
Pour 1/3 of sauce mixture over noodles.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over mixture.
Sprinkle 1/3 pound of grated Mozzarella cheese over top.
Repeat 2 more times for 3 layers.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour.

title: mom's banana cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar with 1 teaspoon hot water.
Add salt and unbeaten eggs; cream well.
Mix together bananas and baking soda until foamy.
Add this mixture to sugar mixture; beat well.
Add milk and flour alternately to banana mixture.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine cake mix flour and yeast in large bowl.
Stir until well blended.
Stir in hot water.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Cut dough in half.
Roll first half of dough into large rectangle on floured surface.
Spread with butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Roll up jelly roll fashion and cut into 12 slices.
Place rolls in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Repeat with second half of dough.
Let rise in pans until doubled.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Mix butter, peanut butter, sugars, egg and vanilla, blending until smooth and creamy.
Add dry ingredients; mix until well blended.
Shape dough into almond sized balls, then roll in sugar.
Place 1 to 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 8 minutes, then remove.
Place an M&M candy or Hershey's Kiss in the center of each cookie.
Put back into the oven for an additional 2 minutes.

title: corn and green bean casserole
directions: Cook frozen vegetables according to package directions; drain well. Saute onion, celery and bell pepper in 2 Tbsp. butter until tender. Combine sauteed mixture, corn, beans, cheese, soup, sour cream, salt and pepper; stir well and spoon into a greased 2 qt. casserole. Combine cracker crumbs, remaining butter, and almonds, if desired. Stir well. Sprinkle crumb mixture over casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: In a casserole or baking dish, layer asparagus, cheese and eggs twice; spoon soup over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until soup bubbles.

title: blonde brownies
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine melted shortening and brown sugar. Stir in eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Spread into greased 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients and mold.
Place in refrigerator to chill. Bake at 350° until done (about 1 1/2 hours).
If desired, meat loaf may be placed in freezer for future baking.

title: w. v. banana muffins
directions: Grease muffin pan.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl. Stir until moist.
Pour the batter into muffin pan cups.
Bake at 375° for about 10 to 12 minutes.
You can add nuts if you wish. Makes 1 dozen.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Mix and let stand 48 hours at room temperature.
After each use, put back 1 to 2 cups flour and mix with lukewarm water.

title: pumpkin nut squares
directions: Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup finely chopped walnuts.

title: souper pork chops
directions: Flour meat; brown in butter.
Remove to casserole.
Cover with cream of mushroom soup, thinned with 1 can water to which the salt and pepper have been added.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, depending on thickness.
If you add mushrooms, add after the soup.

title: my favorite bran muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine bran, wheat germ, flour, baking soda, salt and orange peel.
Set aside.
Combine eggs, honey, molasses, oil, buttermilk and boiling water.
Mix well with dry ingredients. Spoon batter into greased muffin tins filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: whipped cream icing
directions: Cream shortening and oleo very good.
Add sugar and beat.
Add warm milk and beat until creamy.
Add vanilla and continue beating about 5 minutes.
You may add food color if desired.

title: lulu paste dip
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, green pepper and onion.
Cook eggs, vinegar, sugar and salt until thickened (1 to 2 minutes).
Add butter.
Remove from heat.
Combine the two mixtures.
Use as a vegetable dip.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Boil shrimp in enough water to cover. Add celery tops, salt and spices. Cook 10 to 12 minutes. Drain shrimp and cool with cold water.
Peel under cold running water.
Alternate shrimp and sliced onions in shallow dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over shrimp and onions.
Keep in refrigerator at least 24 hours before serving.

title: jay's meat loaf
directions: Mix well and form into a loaf.
Top with bacon.
Pour 2 cups tomato juice over loaf.
Cover with foil.
Remove for last half hour of baking.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: zucchini pancakes(an original creation.)
directions: Combine all ingredients. Add blueberries, if desired.
Stir just until large lumps disappear.
Heat griddle/skillet over medium-low heat.
Lightly grease with safflower oil.
Pour slightly less than 1/4 cup (3 tablespoons) batter for each pancake.
Turn when pancake is golden brown.
Serve with fruit, raw or slightly cooked (peaches, apples, pears or bananas) and maple syrup.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese and sour cream together.
Mix all other ingredients together, saving the nuts and parsley, with the cheese.
Form cheese into balls and roll in the nuts mixed with the parsley flakes.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: quick apple crumb
directions: Spread pie filling in a
9-inch pie pan.
Mix oats and cake mix together.
Spread over pie filling.
Slice butter into thin slices and cover mixture.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken breast fricassee
directions: Sprinkle chicken with pepper; set aside.
Coat Dutch oven with spray.
Place over medium-high heat until hot; add chicken and cook 2 minutes on each side until brown.
Add carrots and next 8 ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes or until tender.
Remove chicken to serving platter. Combine cornstarch and milk and add to vegetable mixture, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer until thickened.
Remove from heat; stir in lemon juice.
Spoon vegetable mixture over chicken.
Yields 4 servings.
Saturated Fat 0.5; Calories per serving:

title: coconut pecan delight
directions: Combine flour, pecans and margarine; mix well.
Press evenly into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown. Cool.
Beat cream cheese until very soft.
Gradually add 1/2 cup milk, blend for 2 minutes.
Add remaining milk and pudding, blend 2 minutes.
Stir in remaining coconut and pecans.
Pour over baked crust.
Spread Cool Whip over pudding.
Sprinkle with coconut and pecans.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: pecan pie
directions: In mixing bowl, beat eggs thoroughly.
Stir in sugar and salt until dissolved.
Stir in corn syrup, butter and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour mixture into an unbaked pie shell. Bake in a 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 325° and bake about 1 hour more or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: yuscan beef stew
directions: Mix soup, broth, wine, beef, tomatoes, carrots, Italian seasoning and garlic in a 3 1/2-quart slow cooker. Cover and cook on low 8 to 9 hours. Stir in beans; turn to high heat and cook 10 minutes. You can cook on high for 4 to 5 hours.

title: gingered sweet potatoes
directions: Arrange potatoes in a steaming rack. Place over boiling water; cover and steam until tender. Remove and place in serving dish. Combine remaining ingredients; blend well. Toss with hot sweet potatoes. Makes 4 servings, 1/2 cup each. Exchange: 1 1/2 starches.

title: potato and onion bake
directions: Layer potato rounds in casserole.
Place onion rounds on each. Then top with oleo.
Sprinkle pepper and salts.
Continue until dish is full.
Cover with lid or foil tightly.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot cornbread
directions: Sift flour, cornmeal, sugar and baking powder into large bowl. Cut in margarine until mixture forms little balls the size of peas. Beat egg in small bowl and stir in buttermilk and carrots.
Pour into dry ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until center springs back when lightly pressed with fingertips. Cool on wire rack.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients until clear and thick.
Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Let cool.
Slice strawberries (drain off any juice) and add to mixture.
Pour into cooked pie shells. Put Cool Whip on top.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt and celery seed over cucumbers, onions and pepper.
Let set 1 hour.
Drain.
Add sugar and vinegar. Refrigerate.

title: baked apples
directions: Place apples into a two quart casserole dish. Add sugar, cinnamon, margarine and water. Bake at 400 degrees for about 1 hour or until apples are tender.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly; season to taste with salt and lemon pepper.
Garnish with pimento.
Chill.
Yields one large salad bowl.
Add additional portions of ingredients and make as much as you like.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Slit skins of potatoes.
Scoop out potatoes into bowl; add margarine and milk.
Mix, then add remaining ingredients.
Fill skins with potato mixture.
Sprinkle on parsley.
Place in a 400° oven until hot.
Serve.

title: surprise snowballs
directions: Beat oleo, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add flour and nuts; blend well.
Chill dough.
Remove foil from Kisses. Shape dough around Kisses using 1 tablespoon dough for each.
Roll to make a ball.
Be sure to cover Kiss completely.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 12 minutes or until set but not browned.
Cool slightly.
Remove carefully to wire rack.
While still warm, sprinkle top with confectioners sugar.
(I put wax paper under the wire racks, put the sugar in a small sieve and shake on the cookies.
Makes them look like the snow fell on them.
Then I save the sugar from the wax paper.)
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes about 50 cookies.

title: strawberries
directions: Mix all together.
For stems put green food coloring in 1/2 cup water.
Put in 4 ounces of slivered almonds.
Shape mixture into strawberries and roll in red sugar.

title: lemon squares
directions: Combine butter, 2 cups flour, powdered sugar and salt.
Pat dough into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Mix eggs, sugar, lemon juice, lemon extract and flour in blender. Pour over baked crust.
Bake 20 minutes; sprinkle with powdered sugar while hot.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: zucchini mushroom quiche
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into "Pammed" quiche or pie dish.
Top if desired with chopped tomatoes.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: chili like wendy's
directions: In a large skillet, crumble and brown beef; drain and add remaining ingredients. Simmer for a few hours.

title: coco coco nut cake
directions: Sift flour; measure and re-sift 3 times with soda, salt and cocoa.
Cream shortening until soft; add sugar and blend thoroughly.
Add beaten eggs and beat vigorously until smooth and fluffy.
Stir in vanilla.
Add flour mixture with buttermilk; add boiling water.

title: spinach dip
directions: In
a medium bowl, combine all ingredients. Cover and chill. Serve in bread bowl or with crackers.

title: crunchy garden vegetable deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs lengthwise in half.
Slip out egg yolks; mash with a fork.
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: gunk
directions: Mix ingredients together in large bowl or storage container. Store in refrigerator when not in use. Wash hands well before playing in it. Recipe may be doubled or tripled for larger groups.

title: mom miner's cherry cheese tarts
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat about 1 or 2 minutes until well blended.
Place 1 vanilla cookie in the bottom of foil cupcake cups; fill cup 1/2 to 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes until set.
Cool and top with cherry pie filling.
Other pie filling may be substituted.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Blend in oil, orange juice, vinegar and salt.
Add to chicken mixture.
Chill one hour.
Drain and add salad dressing and toss together.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: hearty breakfast
